37static inline bool IsZero(const Operand& rt) {
38 if (rt.is_reg()) {
39 return rt.rm() == zero_reg;
40 } else {
41 return rt.immediate() == 0;
42 }
43}

45int MacroAssembler::RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
46 Register exclusion1,
47 Register exclusion2,
48 Register exclusion3) const {
49 int bytes = 0;
50
51 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
52 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
53 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
54
55 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
56 bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
57 }
58
59 return bytes;
60}
61
62int MacroAssembler::PushCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion1,
63 Register exclusion2, Register exclusion3) {
64 int bytes = 0;
65
66 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
67 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
68 MultiPush(list);
69 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
70
71 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
72 MultiPushFPU(kCallerSavedFPU);
73 bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
74 }
75
76 return bytes;
77}
78
79int MacroAssembler::PopCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion1,
80 Register exclusion2, Register exclusion3) {
81 int bytes = 0;
82 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
83 MultiPopFPU(kCallerSavedFPU);
84 bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
85 }
86
87 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
88 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
89 MultiPop(list);
90 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
91
92 return bytes;
93}

95#define __ ACCESS_MASM(masm)
96namespace {
97static void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
98 Register optimized_code_entry,
99 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
100 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
101 // -- a0 : actual argument count
102 // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
103 // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
104 // -----------------------------------
105 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
106 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code_entry, a1, a3, scratch1, scratch2));
107
108 Register closure = a1;
109 Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
110
111 // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
112 // marker field.
113 __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
114 &heal_optimized_code_slot);
115
116 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
117 __ LoadCodePointerField(
118 optimized_code_entry,
119 FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
120
121 // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
122 // runtime to clear it.
123 __ JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
124 &heal_optimized_code_slot);
125
126 // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
127 // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
128 // The feedback vector is no longer used, so re-use it as a scratch
129 // register.
130 __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, closure);
131
132 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
133 __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, optimized_code_entry, kJSEntrypointTag);
134 __ Jump(a2);
135
136 // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
137 // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
138 // and re-enter the closure's code.
139 __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
140 __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
141}

164void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
165 Register optimized_code, Register closure) {
166 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
167 StoreCodePointerField(optimized_code,
168 FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
169 RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, optimized_code,
170 kRAHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore, SmiCheck::kOmit,
171 SlotDescriptor::ForCodePointerSlot());
172}

174void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
175 Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
176 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
177 // -- a0 : actual argument count
178 // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee)
179 // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee)
180 // -----------------------------------
181 {
182 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
183 // Push a copy of the target function, the new target and the actual
184 // argument count.
185 // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
186 SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
187 Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
188 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
189
190 CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
191 // Use the return value before restoring a0
192 LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, a0, kJSEntrypointTag);
193 // Restore target function, new target and actual argument count.
194 Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
195 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
196 SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
197 }
198
199 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
200 Jump(a2);
201}

203// Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
204// is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
205void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
206 Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
207 Label* flags_need_processing) {
208 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
209 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
210 DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
211 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
212 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
213 Lhu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
214 uint32_t kFlagsMask = FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested |
215 FeedbackVector::kFlagsMaybeHasTurbofanCode |
216 FeedbackVector::kFlagsLogNextExecution;
217 if (current_code_kind != CodeKind::MAGLEV) {
218 kFlagsMask |= FeedbackVector::kFlagsMaybeHasMaglevCode;
219 }
220 And(scratch, flags, Operand(kFlagsMask));
221 Branch(flags_need_processing, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
222}
223
224void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
225 Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
226 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
227 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
228 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
229 temps.Include(t0, t1);
230 Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
231 // Check if optimized code is available.
232 {
233 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
234 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
235 And(scratch, flags,
236 Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
237 Branch(&maybe_needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
238 Label::Distance::kNear);
239 }
240 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
241
242 bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
243 {
244 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
245 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
246 And(scratch, flags, Operand(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
247 Branch(&maybe_has_optimized_code, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
248 Label::Distance::kNear);
249 }
250
251 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
252
253 bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
254 Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
255 LoadTaggedField(optimized_code_entry,
256 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
257 FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
258 TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, temps.Acquire(),
259 temps.Acquire());
260}

262void MacroAssembler::LoadRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
263#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
264 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
265 is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
266 DecompressTagged(destination, ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
267 return;
268 }
269#endif
270 // Many roots have addresses that are too large to fit into addition immediate
271 // operands. Evidence suggests that the extra instruction for decompression
272 // costs us more than the load.
273 LoadWord(destination,
274 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
275}
276
277void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
278 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
279 is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
280 li(destination, (int32_t)ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
281 return;
282 }
283 LoadWord(destination,
284 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
285}
286void MacroAssembler::PushCommonFrame(Register marker_reg) {
287 if (marker_reg.is_valid()) {
288 Push(ra, fp, marker_reg);
289 AddWord(fp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
290 } else {
291 Push(ra, fp);
292 Mv(fp, sp);
293 }
294}
295
296void MacroAssembler::PushStandardFrame(Register function_reg) {
297 int offset = -StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset;
298 if (function_reg.is_valid()) {
299 Push(ra, fp, cp, function_reg, kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
300 offset += 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
301 } else {
302 Push(ra, fp, cp, kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
303 offset += kSystemPointerSize;
304 }
305 AddWord(fp, sp, Operand(offset));
306}

308int MacroAssembler::SafepointRegisterStackIndex(int reg_code) {
309 // The registers are pushed starting with the highest encoding,
310 // which means that lowest encodings are closest to the stack pointer.
311 return kSafepointRegisterStackIndexMap[reg_code];
312}

314// Clobbers object, dst, value, and ra, if (ra_status == kRAHasBeenSaved)
315// The register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
316// tag is shifted away.
317void MacroAssembler::RecordWriteField(Register object, int offset,
318 Register value, RAStatus ra_status,
319 SaveFPRegsMode save_fp,
320 SmiCheck smi_check, SlotDescriptor slot) {
321 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value));
322 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
323 // catch stores of Smis.
324 Label done;
325
326 // Skip the barrier if writing a smi.
327 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
328 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
329 }
330
331 // Although the object register is tagged, the offset is relative to the start
332 // of the object, so offset must be a multiple of kTaggedSize.
333 DCHECK(IsAligned(offset, kTaggedSize));
334
335 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
336 Label ok;
337 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
338 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
339 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, scratch));
340 AddWord(scratch, object, offset - kHeapObjectTag);
341 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(kTaggedSize - 1));
342 BranchShort(&ok, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
343 Abort(AbortReason::kUnalignedCellInWriteBarrier);
344 bind(&ok);
345 }
346
347 RecordWrite(object, Operand(offset - kHeapObjectTag), value, ra_status,
348 save_fp, SmiCheck::kOmit, slot);
349
350 bind(&done);
351}

372#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
373void MacroAssembler::ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(Register destination,
374 Register handle,
375 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
376 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
377 // The tag implies which pointer table to use.
378 if (tag == kUnknownIndirectPointerTag) {
379 // In this case we have to rely on the handle marking to determine which
380 // pointer table to use.
381 Label is_trusted_pointer_handle, done;
382 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, handle));
383 And(destination, handle, kCodePointerHandleMarker);
384 Branch(&is_trusted_pointer_handle, eq, destination, Operand(zero_reg));
385 ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
386 Branch(&done);
387 bind(&is_trusted_pointer_handle);
388 ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle,
389 kUnknownIndirectPointerTag);
390 bind(&done);
391 } else if (tag == kCodeIndirectPointerTag) {
392 ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
393 } else {
394 ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
395 }
396}
397
398void MacroAssembler::ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(Register destination,
399 Register handle,
400 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
401 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
402 DCHECK_NE(tag, kCodeIndirectPointerTag);
403 DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
404
405 Register table = destination;
406 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
407 LoadWord(table, MemOperand{kRootRegister,
408 IsolateData::trusted_pointer_table_offset()});
409 SrlWord(handle, handle, kTrustedPointerHandleShift);
410 CalcScaledAddress(destination, table, handle,
411 kTrustedPointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
412 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(destination, 0));
413 // The LSB is used as marking bit by the trusted pointer table, so here we
414 // have to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
415 // Untag the pointer and remove the marking bit in one operation.
416 Register tag_reg = handle;
417 li(tag_reg, Operand(~(tag | kTrustedPointerTableMarkBit)));
418 and_(destination, destination, tag_reg);
419}
420
421void MacroAssembler::ResolveCodePointerHandle(Register destination,
422 Register handle) {
423 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
424 DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
425
426 Register table = destination;
427 li(table, ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_address());
428 SrlWord(handle, handle, kCodePointerHandleShift);
429 CalcScaledAddress(destination, table, handle, kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
430 LoadWord(destination,
431 MemOperand(destination, kCodePointerTableEntryCodeObjectOffset));
432 // The LSB is used as marking bit by the code pointer table, so here we have
433 // to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
434 Or(destination, destination, Operand(kHeapObjectTag));
435}

437void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(Register destination,
438 MemOperand field_operand,
439 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
440 DCHECK_NE(tag, kInvalidEntrypointTag);
441 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
442 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
443 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
444 li(scratch, ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_address());
445 Lwu(destination, field_operand);
446 SrlWord(destination, destination, kCodePointerHandleShift);
447 SllWord(destination, destination, kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
448 AddWord(scratch, scratch, destination);
449 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
450 if (tag != 0) {
451 li(scratch, Operand(tag));
452 xor_(destination, destination, scratch);
453 }
454}
455#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX

457void MacroAssembler::LoadExternalPointerField(Register destination,
458 MemOperand field_operand,
459 ExternalPointerTag tag,
460 Register isolate_root) {
461 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, isolate_root));
462 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
463#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
464 DCHECK_NE(tag, kExternalPointerNullTag);
465 DCHECK(!IsSharedExternalPointerType(tag));
466 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
467 Register external_table = temps.Acquire();
468 if (isolate_root == no_reg) {
469 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
470 isolate_root = kRootRegister;
471 }
472 LoadWord(external_table,
473 MemOperand(isolate_root,
474 IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
475 Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
476 Lwu(destination, field_operand);
477 srli(destination, destination, kExternalPointerIndexShift);
478 slli(destination, destination, kExternalPointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
479 AddWord(external_table, external_table, destination);
480 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(external_table, 0));
481 And(destination, destination, Operand(~tag));
482#else
483 LoadWord(destination, field_operand);
484#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
485}

528void MacroAssembler::CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(Register object, Operand offset,
529 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode) {
530 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
531 RegList registers = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
532 MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
533
534 Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
535 Register slot_address_parameter =
536 WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
537
538 MoveObjectAndSlot(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, object, offset);
539
540 CallBuiltin(Builtins::EphemeronKeyBarrier(fp_mode));
541 MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
542}

544void MacroAssembler::CallIndirectPointerBarrier(Register object, Operand offset,
545 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
546 IndirectPointerTag tag) {

582void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStub(Register object, Register slot_address,
583 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
584 StubCallMode mode) {
585 // Use CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters if the object and slot registers
586 // need to be caller saved.
587 DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(), object);
588 DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), slot_address);
589 if (mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
590 auto wasm_target =
591 static_cast<Address>(wasm::WasmCode::GetRecordWriteBuiltin(fp_mode));
592 Call(wasm_target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
593 } else {
594 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RecordWrite(fp_mode));
595 }
596}

598void MacroAssembler::MoveObjectAndSlot(Register dst_object, Register dst_slot,
599 Register object, Operand offset) {
600 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
601 DCHECK_NE(dst_object, dst_slot);
602 // If `offset` is a register, it cannot overlap with `object`.
603 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!offset.IsImmediate(), offset.rm() != object);
604
605 // If the slot register does not overlap with the object register, we can
606 // overwrite it.
607 if (dst_slot != object) {
608 AddWord(dst_slot, object, offset);
609 mv(dst_object, object);
610 return;
611 }
612
613 DCHECK_EQ(dst_slot, object);
614
615 // If the destination object register does not overlap with the offset
616 // register, we can overwrite it.
617 if (offset.IsImmediate() || (offset.rm() != dst_object)) {
618 mv(dst_object, dst_slot);
619 AddWord(dst_slot, dst_slot, offset);
620 return;
621 }
622
623 DCHECK_EQ(dst_object, offset.rm());
624
625 // We only have `dst_slot` and `dst_object` left as distinct registers so we
626 // have to swap them. We write this as a add+sub sequence to avoid using a
627 // scratch register.
628 AddWord(dst_slot, dst_slot, dst_object);
629 SubWord(dst_object, dst_slot, dst_object);
630}

632// Clobbers object, address, value, and ra, if (ra_status == kRAHasBeenSaved)
633// The register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
634// tag is shifted away.
635void MacroAssembler::RecordWrite(Register object, Operand offset,
636 Register value, RAStatus ra_status,
637 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, SmiCheck smi_check,
638 SlotDescriptor slot) {
639 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value));
640
641 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
642 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
643 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
644 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, temp));
645 AddWord(temp, object, offset);
646#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
647 if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
648 LoadIndirectPointerField(temp, MemOperand(temp, 0),
649 slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
650 } else {
651 DCHECK(slot.contains_direct_pointer());
652 LoadTaggedField(temp, MemOperand(temp, 0));
653 }
654#else
655 LoadTaggedField(temp, MemOperand(temp));
656#endif
657 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongAddressOrValuePassedToRecordWrite, temp,
658 Operand(value));
659 }
660
661 if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
662 return;
663 }
664
665 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
666 // catch stores of smis and stores into the young generation.
667 Label done;
668
669 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
670 DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
671 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
672 }
673
674 {
675 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
676 CheckPageFlag(value, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
677 eq, // In RISC-V, it uses cc for a comparison with 0, so if
678 // no bits are set, and cc is eq, it will branch to done
679 &done);
680
681 CheckPageFlag(object, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
682 eq, // In RISC-V, it uses cc for a comparison with 0, so if
683 // no bits are set, and cc is eq, it will branch to done
684 &done);
685 }
686 // Record the actual write.
687 if (ra_status == kRAHasNotBeenSaved) {
688 push(ra);
689 }
690 Register slot_address = WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
691 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address, value));
692 // TODO(cbruni): Turn offset into int.
693 if (slot.contains_direct_pointer()) {
694 DCHECK(offset.IsImmediate());
695 AddWord(slot_address, object, offset);
696 CallRecordWriteStub(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
697 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
698 } else {
699 DCHECK(slot.contains_indirect_pointer());
700 CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object, offset, fp_mode,
701 slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
702 }
703 if (ra_status == kRAHasNotBeenSaved) {
704 pop(ra);
705 }
706 if (v8_flags.debug_code) li(slot_address, Operand(kZapValue));
707
708 bind(&done);
709}

749void MacroAssembler::Add32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
750 if (rt.is_reg()) {
751 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
752 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
753 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
754 c_addw(rd, rt.rm());
755 } else {
756 addw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
757 }
758 } else {
759 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
760 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) &&
761 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
762 c_addiw(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
763 } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
764 addiw(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
765 } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
766 (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
767 addiw(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
768 addiw(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
769 } else {
770 // li handles the relocation.
771 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
772 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
773 Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
774 addw(rd, rs, scratch);
775 }
776 }
777}

779void MacroAssembler::Sub32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
780 if (rt.is_reg()) {
781 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
782 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
783 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
784 c_subw(rd, rt.rm());
785 } else {
786 subw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
787 }
788 } else {
789 DCHECK(is_int32(rt.immediate()));
790 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
791 (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
792 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
793 c_addiw(
794 rd,
795 static_cast<int8_t>(
796 -rt.immediate())); // No c_subiw instr, use c_addiw(x, y, -imm).
797 } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
798 addiw(rd, rs,
799 static_cast<int32_t>(
800 -rt.immediate())); // No subiw instr, use addiw(x, y, -imm).
801 } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
802 (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
803 addiw(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
804 addiw(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
805 } else {
806 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
807 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
808 if (-rt.immediate() >> 12 == 0 && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
809 // Use load -imm and addu when loading -imm generates one instruction.
810 Li(scratch, -rt.immediate());
811 addw(rd, rs, scratch);
812 } else {
813 // li handles the relocation.
814 Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
815 subw(rd, rs, scratch);
816 }
817 }
818 }
819}

829void MacroAssembler::Sub64(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
830 if (rt.is_reg()) {
831 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
832 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
833 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
834 c_sub(rd, rt.rm());
835 } else {
836 sub(rd, rs, rt.rm());
837 }
838 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
839 (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
840 (rt.immediate() != 0) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
841 c_addi(rd,
842 static_cast<int8_t>(
843 -rt.immediate())); // No c_subi instr, use c_addi(x, y, -imm).
844
845 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(-rt.immediate()) &&
846 (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
847 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
848 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
849 c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(-rt.immediate()));
850 } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
851 addi(rd, rs,
852 static_cast<int32_t>(
853 -rt.immediate())); // No subi instr, use addi(x, y, -imm).
854 } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
855 (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
856 addi(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
857 addi(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
858 } else {
859 int li_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(rt.immediate());
860 int li_neg_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(-rt.immediate());
861 if (li_neg_count < li_count && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
862 // Use load -imm and add when loading -imm generates one instruction.
863 DCHECK(rt.immediate() != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
864 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
865 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
866 li(scratch, Operand(-rt.immediate()));
867 add(rd, rs, scratch);
868 } else {
869 // li handles the relocation.
870 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
871 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
872 li(scratch, rt);
873 sub(rd, rs, scratch);
874 }
875 }

1577void MacroAssembler::Ror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1578 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1579 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1580 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1581 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1582 negw(scratch, rt.rm());
1583 sllw(scratch, rs, scratch);
1584 srlw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1585 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1586 sext_w(rd, rd);
1587 } else {
1588 int64_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1589 if (ror_value == 0) {
1590 Mv(rd, rs);
1591 return;
1592 } else if (ror_value < 0) {
1593 ror_value += 32;
1594 }
1595 srliw(scratch, rs, ror_value);
1596 slliw(rd, rs, 32 - ror_value);
1597 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1598 sext_w(rd, rd);
1599 }
1600}

1704void MacroAssembler::CalcScaledAddress(Register rd, Register rt, Register rs,
1705 uint8_t sa) {
1706 DCHECK(sa >= 1 && sa <= 31);
1707 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBA)) {
1708 switch (sa) {
1709 case 1:
1710 sh1add(rd, rs, rt);
1711 return;
1712 case 2:
1713 sh2add(rd, rs, rt);
1714 return;
1715 case 3:
1716 sh3add(rd, rs, rt);
1717 return;
1718 default:
1719 break;
1720 }
1721 }
1722 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1723 Register tmp = rd == rt ? temps.Acquire() : rd;
1724 DCHECK(tmp != rt);
1725 slli(tmp, rs, sa);
1726 AddWord(rd, rt, tmp);
1727 return;
1728}

1730// ------------Pseudo-instructions-------------
1731// Change endianness
1732#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
1733void MacroAssembler::ByteSwap(Register rd, Register rs, int operand_size,
1734 Register scratch) {
1735 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
1736 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
1737 DCHECK(operand_size == 4 || operand_size == 8);
1738 if (operand_size == 4) {
1739 // Uint32_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF;
1740 // x0 = (x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16);
1741 // x0 = (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8));
1742 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1743 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1744 DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1745 Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1746 Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1747 Register x2 = scratch;
1748 li(x1, 0x00FF00FF);
1749 slliw(x0, rs, 16);
1750 srliw(rd, rs, 16);
1751 or_(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16
1752 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF
1753 slliw(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1754 slliw(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00
1755 and_(rd, x0, x1); // x0 & 0xFF00FF00
1756 srliw(rd, rd, 8);
1757 or_(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1758 } else {
1759 // uinx24_t x1 = 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFl;
1760 // uinx24_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFl;
1761 // x0 = (x0 << 32 | x0 >> 32);
1762 // x0 = (x0 & x1) << 16 | (x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16;
1763 // x0 = (x0 & x1) << 8 | (x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8;
1764 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1765 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1766 DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1767 Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1768 Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1769 Register x2 = scratch;
1770 li(x1, 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFl);
1771 slli(x0, rs, 32);
1772 srli(rd, rs, 32);
1773 or_(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 32 | x0 >> 32
1774 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF
1775 slli(x2, x2, 16); // x2 <- (x0 & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF) << 16
1776 slli(x1, x1, 16); // x1 <- 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000
1777 and_(rd, x0, x1); // rd <- x0 & 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000
1778 srli(rd, rd, 16); // rd <- x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16
1779 or_(x0, rd, x2); // (x0 & x1) << 16 | (x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16;
1780 li(x1, 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFl);
1781 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF
1782 slli(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1783 slli(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00FF00FF00
1784 and_(rd, x0, x1);
1785 srli(rd, rd, 8); // rd <- (x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8
1786 or_(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1787 }
1788}
1789
1790#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
1791void MacroAssembler::ByteSwap(Register rd, Register rs, int operand_size,
1792 Register scratch) {
1793 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
1794 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
1795 // Uint32_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF;
1796 // x0 = (x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16);
1797 // x0 = (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8));
1798 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1799 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1800 DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1801 Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1802 Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1803 Register x2 = scratch;
1804 li(x1, 0x00FF00FF);
1805 slli(x0, rs, 16);
1806 srli(rd, rs, 16);
1807 or_(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16
1808 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF
1809 slli(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1810 slli(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00
1811 and_(rd, x0, x1); // x0 & 0xFF00FF00
1812 srli(rd, rd, 8);
1813 or_(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1814}
1815#endif
1816
1817template <int NBYTES, bool LOAD_SIGNED>
1818void MacroAssembler::LoadNBytes(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs,
1819 Register scratch) {
1820 DCHECK(rd != rs.rm() && rd != scratch);
1821 DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
1822
1823 // load the most significant byte
1824 if (LOAD_SIGNED) {
1825 lb(rd, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1826 } else {
1827 lbu(rd, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1828 }
1829
1830 // load remaining (nbytes-1) bytes from higher to lower
1831 slli(rd, rd, 8 * (NBYTES - 1));
1832 for (int i = (NBYTES - 2); i >= 0; i--) {
1833 lbu(scratch, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + i);
1834 if (i) slli(scratch, scratch, i * 8);
1835 or_(rd, rd, scratch);
1836 }
1837}
1838
1839template <int NBYTES, bool LOAD_SIGNED>
1840void MacroAssembler::LoadNBytesOverwritingBaseReg(const MemOperand& rs,
1841 Register scratch0,
1842 Register scratch1) {
1843 // This function loads nbytes from memory specified by rs and into rs.rm()
1844 DCHECK(rs.rm() != scratch0 && rs.rm() != scratch1 && scratch0 != scratch1);
1845 DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
1846
1847 // load the most significant byte
1848 if (LOAD_SIGNED) {
1849 lb(scratch0, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1850 } else {
1851 lbu(scratch0, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1852 }
1853
1854 // load remaining (nbytes-1) bytes from higher to lower
1855 slli(scratch0, scratch0, 8 * (NBYTES - 1));
1856 for (int i = (NBYTES - 2); i >= 0; i--) {
1857 lbu(scratch1, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + i);
1858 if (i) {
1859 slli(scratch1, scratch1, i * 8);
1860 or_(scratch0, scratch0, scratch1);
1861 } else {
1862 // write to rs.rm() when processing the last byte
1863 or_(rs.rm(), scratch0, scratch1);
1864 }
1865 }
1866}
1867
1868template <int NBYTES, bool IS_SIGNED>
1869void MacroAssembler::UnalignedLoadHelper(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
1870 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1871 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1872
1873 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
1874 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
1875 MemOperand source = rs;
1876 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
1877 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
1878 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
1879 NBYTES - 1);
1880
1881 // Since source.rm() is scratch_base, assume rd != source.rm()
1882 DCHECK(rd != source.rm());
1883 Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
1884 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rd, source, scratch_other);
1885 } else {
1886 // no need to adjust base-and-offset
1887 if (rd != rs.rm()) {
1888 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1889 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rd, rs, scratch);
1890 } else { // rd == rs.rm()
1891 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1892 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
1893 LoadNBytesOverwritingBaseReg<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rs, scratch, scratch2);
1894 }
1895 }
1896}

1898#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
1899template <int NBYTES>
1900void MacroAssembler::UnalignedFLoadHelper(FPURegister frd, const MemOperand& rs,
1901 Register scratch_base) {
1902 DCHECK(NBYTES == 4 || NBYTES == 8);
1903 DCHECK_NE(scratch_base, rs.rm());
1904 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1905 MemOperand source = rs;
1906 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
1907 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
1908 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
1909 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
1910 NBYTES - 1);
1911 }
1912 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1913 Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
1914 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1915 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
1916 scratch_other != rs.rm());
1917 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
1918 if (NBYTES == 4)
1919 fmv_w_x(frd, scratch);
1920 else
1921 fmv_d_x(frd, scratch);
1922}

1930 MemOperand source = rs;
1931 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
1932 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
1933 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
1934 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
1935 NBYTES - 1);
1936 }
1937 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1938 Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
1939 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1940 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
1941 scratch_other != rs.rm());

1946void MacroAssembler::UnalignedDoubleHelper(FPURegister frd,
1947 const MemOperand& rs,
1948 Register scratch_base) {
1949 DCHECK_NE(scratch_base, rs.rm());
1950 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1951 MemOperand source = rs;
1952 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, 8 - 1)) {
1953 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
1954 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
1955 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
1956 8 - 1);
1957 }
1958 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1959 Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
1960 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1961 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
1962 scratch_other != rs.rm());
1963 LoadNBytes<4, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
1964 SubWord(sp, sp, 8);
1965 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
1966 source.set_offset(source.offset() + 4);
1967 LoadNBytes<4, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
1968 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
1969 LoadDouble(frd, MemOperand(sp, 0));
1970 AddWord(sp, sp, 8);
1971}

1974template <int NBYTES>
1975void MacroAssembler::UnalignedStoreHelper(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs,
1976 Register scratch_other) {
1977 DCHECK(scratch_other != rs.rm());
1978 DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
1979 MemOperand source = rs;
1980 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1981 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
1982 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
1983 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
1984 DCHECK(scratch_base != rd && scratch_base != rs.rm());
1985 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
1986 NBYTES - 1);
1987 }
1988
1989 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1990 if (scratch_other == no_reg) {
1991 if (temps.hasAvailable()) {
1992 scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
1993 } else {
1994 push(t2);
1995 scratch_other = t2;
1996 }
1997 }
1998
1999 DCHECK(scratch_other != rd && scratch_other != rs.rm() &&
2000 scratch_other != source.rm());
2001
2002 sb(rd, source.rm(), source.offset());
2003 for (size_t i = 1; i <= (NBYTES - 1); i++) {
2004 srli(scratch_other, rd, i * 8);
2005 sb(scratch_other, source.rm(), source.offset() + i);
2006 }
2007 if (scratch_other == t2) {
2008 pop(t2);
2009 }
2010}

2015 const MemOperand& rs,
2016 Register scratch) {
2017 DCHECK(NBYTES == 8 || NBYTES == 4);
2018 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs.rm());

2021 } else {

2036void MacroAssembler::UnalignedDStoreHelper(FPURegister frd,
2037 const MemOperand& rs,
2038 Register scratch) {
2039 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs.rm());
2040 Sub32(sp, sp, 8);
2041 StoreDouble(frd, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2042 Lw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2043 UnalignedStoreHelper<4>(scratch, rs);
2044 Lw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
2045 MemOperand source = rs;
2046 source.set_offset(source.offset() + 4);
2047 UnalignedStoreHelper<4>(scratch, source);
2048 Add32(sp, sp, 8);
2049}

2052template <typename Reg_T, typename Func>
2053void MacroAssembler::AlignedLoadHelper(Reg_T target, const MemOperand& rs,
2054 Func generator) {
2055 MemOperand source = rs;
2056 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2057 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2058 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(source)) {
2059 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2060 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm());
2061 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch);
2062 }
2063 generator(target, source);
2064}
2065
2066template <typename Reg_T, typename Func>
2067void MacroAssembler::AlignedStoreHelper(Reg_T value, const MemOperand& rs,
2068 Func generator) {
2069 MemOperand source = rs;
2070 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2071 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2072 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(source)) {
2073 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2074 // make sure scratch does not overwrite value
2075 if (std::is_same<Reg_T, Register>::value)
2076 DCHECK(scratch.code() != value.code());
2077 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm());
2078 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch);
2079 }
2080 generator(value, source);
2081}

2382void MacroAssembler::li(Register dst, Handle<HeapObject> value,
2383 RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
2384 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
2385 // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
2386 // embedding the relocatable value.
2387 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
2388 IndirectLoadConstant(dst, value);
2389 return;
2390 } else if (RelocInfo::IsCompressedEmbeddedObject(rmode)) {
2391 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(value);
2392 DCHECK(is_uint32(index));
2393 li(dst, Operand(index, rmode));
2394 } else {
2395 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsFullEmbeddedObject(rmode));
2396 li(dst, Operand(value.address(), rmode));
2397 }
2398}
2399
2400void MacroAssembler::li(Register dst, ExternalReference value, LiFlags mode) {
2401 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
2402 // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
2403 // embedding the relocatable value.
2404 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
2405 IndirectLoadExternalReference(dst, value);
2406 return;
2407 }
2408 li(dst, Operand(value), mode);
2409}
2410
2411static inline int InstrCountForLiLower32Bit(int64_t value) {
2412 int64_t Hi20 = ((value + 0x800) >> 12);
2413 int64_t Lo12 = value << 52 >> 52;
2414 if (Hi20 == 0 || Lo12 == 0) {
2415 return 1;
2416 }
2417 return 2;
2418}
2419
2420int MacroAssembler::InstrCountForLi64Bit(int64_t value) {
2421 if (is_int32(value + 0x800)) {
2422 return InstrCountForLiLower32Bit(value);
2423 } else {
2424 return RV_li_count(value);
2425 }
2426 UNREACHABLE();
2427 return INT_MAX;
2428}
2429
2430void MacroAssembler::li_optimized(Register rd, Operand j, LiFlags mode) {
2431 DCHECK(!j.is_reg());
2432 DCHECK(!MustUseReg(j.rmode()));
2433 DCHECK(mode == OPTIMIZE_SIZE);
2434 Li(rd, j.immediate());
2435}
2436
2437void MacroAssembler::li(Register rd, Operand j, LiFlags mode) {
2438 DCHECK(!j.is_reg());
2439 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2440 if (!MustUseReg(j.rmode()) && mode == OPTIMIZE_SIZE) {
2441 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2442 int count = RV_li_count(j.immediate(), temps.hasAvailable());
2443 int reverse_count = RV_li_count(~j.immediate(), temps.hasAvailable());
2444 if (v8_flags.riscv_constant_pool && count >= 4 && reverse_count >= 4) {
2445 // Ld/Lw a Address from a constant pool.
2446#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2447 RecordEntry((uint32_t)j.immediate(), j.rmode());
2448#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2449 RecordEntry((uint64_t)j.immediate(), j.rmode());
2450#endif
2451 auipc(rd, 0);
2452 // Record a value into constant pool.
2453 LoadWord(rd, MemOperand(rd, 0));
2454 } else {
2455 if ((count - reverse_count) > 1) {
2456 Li(rd, ~j.immediate());
2457 not_(rd, rd);
2458 } else {
2459 Li(rd, j.immediate());
2460 }
2461 }
2462 } else if (MustUseReg(j.rmode())) {
2463 int64_t immediate;
2464 if (j.IsHeapNumberRequest()) {
2465 RequestHeapNumber(j.heap_number_request());
2466 immediate = 0;
2467 } else {
2468 immediate = j.immediate();
2469 }
2470
2471 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode(), immediate);
2472 li_ptr(rd, immediate);
2473 } else if (mode == ADDRESS_LOAD) {
2474 // We always need the same number of instructions as we may need to patch
2475 // this code to load another value which may need all 6 instructions.
2476 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2477 li_ptr(rd, j.immediate());
2478 } else { // Always emit the same 48 bit instruction
2479 // sequence.
2480 li_ptr(rd, j.immediate());
2481 }
2482}
2483
2484static RegList t_regs = {t0, t1, t2, t3, t4, t5, t6};
2485static RegList a_regs = {a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7};
2486static RegList s_regs = {s1, s2, s3, s4, s5, s6, s7, s8, s9, s10, s11};
2487
2488void MacroAssembler::MultiPush(RegList regs) {
2489 int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
2490 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kSystemPointerSize;
2491
2492#define TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(reg) \
2493 if (regs.has(reg)) { \
2494 stack_offset -= kSystemPointerSize; \
2495 StoreWord(reg, MemOperand(sp, stack_offset)); \
2496 regs.clear(reg); \
2497 }
2498
2499#define T_REGS(V) V(t6) V(t5) V(t4) V(t3) V(t2) V(t1) V(t0)
2500#define A_REGS(V) V(a7) V(a6) V(a5) V(a4) V(a3) V(a2) V(a1) V(a0)
2501#define S_REGS(V) \
2502 V(s11) V(s10) V(s9) V(s8) V(s7) V(s6) V(s5) V(s4) V(s3) V(s2) V(s1)
2503
2504 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_offset));
2505
2506 // Certain usage of MultiPush requires that registers are pushed onto the
2507 // stack in a particular: ra, fp, sp, gp, .... (basically in the decreasing
2508 // order of register numbers according to MIPS register numbers)
2509 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(ra);
2510 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(fp);
2511 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(sp);
2512 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(gp);
2513 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(tp);
2514 if (!(regs & s_regs).is_empty()) {
2515 S_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2516 }
2517 if (!(regs & a_regs).is_empty()) {
2518 A_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2519 }
2520 if (!(regs & t_regs).is_empty()) {
2521 T_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2522 }
2523
2524 DCHECK(regs.is_empty());
2525
2526#undef TEST_AND_PUSH_REG
2527#undef T_REGS
2528#undef A_REGS
2529#undef S_REGS
2530}
2531
2532void MacroAssembler::MultiPop(RegList regs) {
2533 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
2534
2535#define TEST_AND_POP_REG(reg) \
2536 if (regs.has(reg)) { \
2537 LoadWord(reg, MemOperand(sp, stack_offset)); \
2538 stack_offset += kSystemPointerSize; \
2539 regs.clear(reg); \
2540 }
2541
2542#define T_REGS(V) V(t0) V(t1) V(t2) V(t3) V(t4) V(t5) V(t6)
2543#define A_REGS(V) V(a0) V(a1) V(a2) V(a3) V(a4) V(a5) V(a6) V(a7)
2544#define S_REGS(V) \
2545 V(s1) V(s2) V(s3) V(s4) V(s5) V(s6) V(s7) V(s8) V(s9) V(s10) V(s11)
2546
2547 // MultiPop pops from the stack in reverse order as MultiPush
2548 if (!(regs & t_regs).is_empty()) {
2549 T_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2550 }
2551 if (!(regs & a_regs).is_empty()) {
2552 A_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2553 }
2554 if (!(regs & s_regs).is_empty()) {
2555 S_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2556 }
2557 TEST_AND_POP_REG(tp);
2558 TEST_AND_POP_REG(gp);
2559 TEST_AND_POP_REG(sp);
2560 TEST_AND_POP_REG(fp);
2561 TEST_AND_POP_REG(ra);
2562
2563 DCHECK(regs.is_empty());
2564
2565 addi(sp, sp, stack_offset);
2566
2567#undef TEST_AND_POP_REG
2568#undef T_REGS
2569#undef S_REGS
2570#undef A_REGS
2571}
2572
2573void MacroAssembler::MultiPushFPU(DoubleRegList regs) {
2574 int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
2575 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kDoubleSize;
2576
2577 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_offset));
2578 for (int16_t i = kNumRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
2579 if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
2580 stack_offset -= kDoubleSize;
2581 StoreDouble(FPURegister::from_code(i), MemOperand(sp, stack_offset));
2582 }
2583 }
2584}
2585
2586void MacroAssembler::MultiPopFPU(DoubleRegList regs) {
2587 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
2588
2589 for (int16_t i = 0; i < kNumRegisters; i++) {
2590 if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
2591 LoadDouble(FPURegister::from_code(i), MemOperand(sp, stack_offset));
2592 stack_offset += kDoubleSize;
2593 }
2594 }
2595 addi(sp, sp, stack_offset);
2596}

2598#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2599void MacroAssembler::AddPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2600 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2601 Register right_low, Register right_high,
2602 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2603 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2604 Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2605 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2606
2607 Add32(scratch1, left_low, right_low);
2608 // Save the carry
2609 Sltu(scratch3, scratch1, left_low);
2610 Add32(scratch2, left_high, right_high);
2611
2612 // Output higher 32 bits + carry
2613 Add32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2614 Move(dst_low, scratch1);
2615}

2617void MacroAssembler::SubPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2618 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2619 Register right_low, Register right_high,
2620 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2621 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2622 Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2623 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2624
2625 // Check if we need a borrow
2626 Sltu(scratch3, left_low, right_low);
2627 Sub32(scratch1, left_low, right_low);
2628 Sub32(scratch2, left_high, right_high);
2629
2630 // Output higher 32 bits - borrow
2631 Sub32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2632 Move(dst_low, scratch1);
2633}

2655void MacroAssembler::MulPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2656 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2657 Register right_low, Register right_high,
2658 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2659 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2660 Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2661 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2662 if (dst_low == right_low) {
2663 mv(scratch1, right_low);
2664 }
2665 Mul(scratch3, left_low, right_high);
2666 // NOTE: do not move these around, recommended sequence is MULH-MUL
2667 // LL * RL : higher 32 bits
2668 mulhu(scratch2, left_low, right_low);
2669 // LL * RL : lower 32 bits
2670 Mul(dst_low, left_low, right_low);
2671 // (LL * RH) + (LL * RL : higher 32 bits)
2672 Add32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch3);
2673 if (dst_low != right_low) {
2674 Mul(scratch3, left_high, right_low);
2675 } else {
2676 Mul(scratch3, left_high, scratch1);
2677 }
2678 Add32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2679}
2680
2681void MacroAssembler::ShlPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2682 Register src_low, Register src_high,
2683 Register shift, Register scratch1,
2684 Register scratch2) {
2685 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2686 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2687 Label done;
2688 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2689 Register scratch3 = no_reg;
2690 if (dst_low == src_low) {
2691 scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2692 mv(scratch3, src_low);
2693 }
2694 And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
2695 // LOW32 << shamt
2696 sll(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
2697 // HIGH32 << shamt
2698 sll(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
2699
2700 // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
2701 Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
2702
2703 // LOW32 >> (32 - shamt)
2704 li(scratch2, 32);
2705 Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2706 if (dst_low == src_low) {
2707 srl(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
2708 } else {
2709 srl(scratch1, src_low, scratch2);
2710 }
2711
2712 // (HIGH32 << shamt) | (LOW32 >> (32 - shamt))
2713 Or(dst_high, dst_high, scratch1);
2714
2715 // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
2716 // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
2717 // is set
2718 And(scratch1, shift, 32);
2719 Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
2720 Move(dst_high, dst_low);
2721 Move(dst_low, zero_reg);
2722
2723 bind(&done);
2724}
2725
2726void MacroAssembler::ShlPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2727 Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
2728 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2729 DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
2730 DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_low);
2731 DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_low);
2732 shift &= 0x3F;
2733 if (shift == 0) {
2734 Move(dst_high, src_high);
2735 Move(dst_low, src_low);
2736 } else if (shift == 32) {
2737 Move(dst_high, src_low);
2738 li(dst_low, Operand(0));
2739 } else if (shift > 32) {
2740 shift &= 0x1F;
2741 slli(dst_high, src_low, shift);
2742 li(dst_low, Operand(0));
2743 } else {
2744 slli(dst_high, src_high, shift);
2745 slli(dst_low, src_low, shift);
2746 srli(scratch1, src_low, 32 - shift);
2747 Or(dst_high, dst_high, scratch1);
2748 }
2749}

2751void MacroAssembler::ShrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2752 Register src_low, Register src_high,
2753 Register shift, Register scratch1,
2754 Register scratch2) {
2755 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2756 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2757 Label done;
2758 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2759 Register scratch3 = no_reg;
2760 if (dst_high == src_high) {
2761 scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2762 mv(scratch3, src_high);
2763 }
2764 And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
2765 // HIGH32 >> shamt
2766 srl(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
2767 // LOW32 >> shamt
2768 srl(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
2769
2770 // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
2771 Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
2772
2773 // HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)
2774 li(scratch2, 32);
2775 Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2776 if (dst_high == src_high) {
2777 sll(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
2778 } else {
2779 sll(scratch1, src_high, scratch2);
2780 }
2781
2782 // (HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)) | (LOW32 >> shamt)
2783 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
2784
2785 // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
2786 // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
2787 // is set
2788 And(scratch1, shift, 32);
2789 Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
2790 Move(dst_low, dst_high);
2791 Move(dst_high, zero_reg);
2792
2793 bind(&done);
2794}

2796void MacroAssembler::ShrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2797 Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
2798 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2799 DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
2800 DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_high);
2801 DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_high);
2802 shift &= 0x3F;
2803 if (shift == 32) {
2804 mv(dst_low, src_high);
2805 li(dst_high, Operand(0));
2806 } else if (shift > 32) {
2807 shift &= 0x1F;
2808 srli(dst_low, src_high, shift);
2809 li(dst_high, Operand(0));
2810 } else if (shift == 0) {
2811 Move(dst_low, src_low);
2812 Move(dst_high, src_high);
2813 } else {
2814 srli(dst_low, src_low, shift);
2815 srli(dst_high, src_high, shift);
2816 slli(scratch1, src_high, 32 - shift);
2817 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
2818 }
2819}

2821void MacroAssembler::SarPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2822 Register src_low, Register src_high,
2823 Register shift, Register scratch1,
2824 Register scratch2) {
2825 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2826 Label done;
2827 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2828 Register scratch3 = no_reg;
2829 if (dst_high == src_high) {
2830 scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2831 mv(scratch3, src_high);
2832 }
2833 And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
2834 // HIGH32 >> shamt (arithmetic)
2835 sra(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
2836 // LOW32 >> shamt (logical)
2837 srl(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
2838
2839 // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
2840 Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
2841
2842 // HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)
2843 li(scratch2, 32);
2844 Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2845 if (dst_high == src_high) {
2846 sll(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
2847 } else {
2848 sll(scratch1, src_high, scratch2);
2849 }
2850 // (HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)) | (LOW32 >> shamt)
2851 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
2852
2853 // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
2854 // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
2855 // is set
2856 And(scratch1, shift, 32);
2857 Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
2858 Move(dst_low, dst_high);
2859 Sra32(dst_high, dst_high, 31);
2860
2861 bind(&done);
2862}
2863
2864void MacroAssembler::SarPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2865 Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
2866 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2867 DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
2868 DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_high);
2869 DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_high);
2870 shift = shift & 0x3F;
2871 if (shift == 0) {
2872 mv(dst_low, src_low);
2873 mv(dst_high, src_high);
2874 } else if (shift < 32) {
2875 srli(dst_low, src_low, shift);
2876 srai(dst_high, src_high, shift);
2877 slli(scratch1, src_high, 32 - shift);
2878 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
2879 } else if (shift == 32) {
2880 srai(dst_high, src_high, 31);
2881 mv(dst_low, src_high);
2882 } else {
2883 srai(dst_high, src_high, 31);
2884 srai(dst_low, src_high, shift - 32);
2885 }
2886}

2888
2889void MacroAssembler::ExtractBits(Register rt, Register rs, uint16_t pos,
2890 uint16_t size, bool sign_extend) {
2891#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2892 DCHECK(pos < 64 && 0 < size && size <= 64 && 0 < pos + size &&
2893 pos + size <= 64);
2894 slli(rt, rs, 64 - (pos + size));
2895 if (sign_extend) {
2896 srai(rt, rt, 64 - size);
2897 } else {
2898 srli(rt, rt, 64 - size);
2899 }
2900#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2901 DCHECK_LT(pos, 32);
2902 DCHECK_GT(size, 0);
2903 DCHECK_LE(size, 32);
2904 DCHECK_GT(pos + size, 0);
2905 DCHECK_LE(pos + size, 32);
2906 slli(rt, rs, 32 - (pos + size));
2907 if (sign_extend) {
2908 srai(rt, rt, 32 - size);
2909 } else {
2910 srli(rt, rt, 32 - size);
2911 }
2912#endif
2913}
2914
2915void MacroAssembler::InsertBits(Register dest, Register source, Register pos,
2916 int size) {
2917#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2918 DCHECK_LT(size, 64);
2919#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2920 DCHECK_LT(size, 32);
2921#endif
2922 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2923 Register mask = temps.Acquire();
2924 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2925 Register source_ = temps.Acquire();
2926 // Create a mask of the length=size.
2927 li(mask, 1);
2928 slli(mask, mask, size);
2929 addi(mask, mask, -1);
2930 and_(source_, mask, source);
2931 sll(source_, source_, pos);
2932 // Make a mask containing 0's. 0's start at "pos" with length=size.
2933 sll(mask, mask, pos);
2934 not_(mask, mask);
2935 // cut area for insertion of source.
2936 and_(dest, mask, dest);
2937 // insert source
2938 or_(dest, dest, source_);
2939}

2975template <typename CvtFunc>
2976void MacroAssembler::RoundFloatingPointToInteger(Register rd, FPURegister fs,
2977 Register result,
2978 CvtFunc fcvt_generator) {
2979 // Save csr_fflags to scratch & clear exception flags
2980 if (result.is_valid()) {
2981 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2982 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2983 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2984
2985 int exception_flags = kInvalidOperation;
2986 csrrci(scratch, csr_fflags, exception_flags);
2987
2988 // actual conversion instruction
2989 fcvt_generator(this, rd, fs);
2990
2991 // check kInvalidOperation flag (out-of-range, NaN)
2992 // set result to 1 if normal, otherwise set result to 0 for abnormal
2993 frflags(result);
2994 andi(result, result, exception_flags);
2995 seqz(result, result); // result <-- 1 (normal), result <-- 0 (abnormal)
2996
2997 // restore csr_fflags
2998 csrw(csr_fflags, scratch);
2999 } else {
3000 // actual conversion instruction
3001 fcvt_generator(this, rd, fs);
3002 }
3003}

3119// According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3120// the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3121// rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3122// round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3123// handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3124#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3125template <typename F>
3126void MacroAssembler::RoundHelper(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src,
3127 FPURegister fpu_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm) {
3128 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3129 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3130 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3131
3132 DCHECK((std::is_same<float, F>::value) || (std::is_same<double, F>::value));
3133 // Need at least two FPRs, so check against dst == src == fpu_scratch
3134 DCHECK(!(dst == src && dst == fpu_scratch));
3135
3136 const int kFloatMantissaBits =
3137 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32MantissaBits : kFloat64MantissaBits;
3138 const int kFloatExponentBits =
3139 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBits : kFloat64ExponentBits;
3140 const int kFloatExponentBias =
3141 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBias : kFloat64ExponentBias;
3142 Label done;
3143
3144 {
3145 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3146 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3147 // extract exponent value of the source floating-point to scratch
3148 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3149 fmv_x_d(scratch, src);
3150 } else {
3151 fmv_x_w(scratch, src);
3152 }
3153 ExtractBits(scratch2, scratch, kFloatMantissaBits, kFloatExponentBits);
3154 }
3155
3156 // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3157 // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3158 // generating another branch)
3159 if (dst != src) {
3160 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3161 fmv_d(dst, src);
3162 } else {
3163 fmv_s(dst, src);
3164 }
3165 }
3166 {
3167 Label not_NaN;
3168 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3169 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3170 // According to the wasm spec
3171 // (https://webassembly.github.io/spec/core/exec/numerics.html#aux-nans)
3172 // if input is canonical NaN, then output is canonical NaN, and if input is
3173 // any other NaN, then output is any NaN with most significant bit of
3174 // payload is 1. In RISC-V, feq_d will set scratch to 0 if src is a NaN. If
3175 // src is not a NaN, branch to the label and do nothing, but if it is,
3176 // fmin_d will set dst to the canonical NaN.
3177 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3178 feq_d(scratch, src, src);
3179 bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3180 fmin_d(dst, src, src);
3181 } else {
3182 feq_s(scratch, src, src);
3183 bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3184 fmin_s(dst, src, src);
3185 }
3186 bind(&not_NaN);
3187 }
3188
3189 // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3190 // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3191 // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3192 // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3193 // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3194 // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3195 // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3196 Branch(&done, greater_equal, scratch2,
3197 Operand(kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits));
3198
3199 // Actual rounding is needed along this path
3200
3201 // old_src holds the original input, needed for the case of src == dst
3202 FPURegister old_src = src;
3203 if (src == dst) {
3204 DCHECK(fpu_scratch != dst);
3205 Move(fpu_scratch, src);
3206 old_src = fpu_scratch;
3207 }
3208
3209 // Since only input whose real exponent value is less than kMantissaBits
3210 // (i.e., 23 or 52-bits) falls into this path, the value range of the input
3211 // falls into that of 23- or 53-bit integers. So we round the input to integer
3212 // values, then convert them back to floating-point.
3213 {
3214 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3215 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3216 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3217 fcvt_l_d(scratch, src, frm);
3218 fcvt_d_l(dst, scratch, frm);
3219 } else {
3220 fcvt_w_s(scratch, src, frm);
3221 fcvt_s_w(dst, scratch, frm);
3222 }
3223 }
3224 // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3225 // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3226 // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3227 // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3228 // Therefore, we use sign-bit injection to produce +/-0 correctly. Instead of
3229 // testing for zero w/ a branch, we just insert sign-bit for everyone on this
3230 // path (this is where old_src is needed)
3231 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3232 fsgnj_d(dst, dst, old_src);
3233 } else {
3234 fsgnj_s(dst, dst, old_src);
3235 }
3236
3237 bind(&done);
3238}
3239#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3240// According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3241// the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3242// rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3243// round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3244// handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3245void MacroAssembler::RoundFloat(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src,
3246 FPURegister fpu_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm) {
3247 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3248 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3249 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3250
3251 // Need at least two FPRs, so check against dst == src == fpu_scratch
3252 DCHECK(!(dst == src && dst == fpu_scratch));
3253
3254 const int kFloatMantissaBits = kFloat32MantissaBits;
3255 const int kFloatExponentBits = kFloat32ExponentBits;
3256 const int kFloatExponentBias = kFloat32ExponentBias;
3257 Label done;
3258
3259 {
3260 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3261 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3262 // extract exponent value of the source floating-point to scratch
3263 fmv_x_w(scratch, src);
3264 ExtractBits(scratch2, scratch, kFloatMantissaBits, kFloatExponentBits);
3265 }
3266
3267 // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3268 // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3269 // generating another branch)
3270 if (dst != src) {
3271 fmv_s(dst, src);
3272 }
3273 {
3274 Label not_NaN;
3275 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3276 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3277 // According to the wasm spec
3278 // (https://webassembly.github.io/spec/core/exec/numerics.html#aux-nans)
3279 // if input is canonical NaN, then output is canonical NaN, and if input is
3280 // any other NaN, then output is any NaN with most significant bit of
3281 // payload is 1. In RISC-V, feq_d will set scratch to 0 if src is a NaN. If
3282 // src is not a NaN, branch to the label and do nothing, but if it is,
3283 // fmin_d will set dst to the canonical NaN.
3284 feq_s(scratch, src, src);
3285 bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3286 fmin_s(dst, src, src);
3287 bind(&not_NaN);
3288 }
3289
3290 // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3291 // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3292 // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3293 // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3294 // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3295 // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3296 // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3297 Branch(&done, greater_equal, scratch2,
3298 Operand(kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits));
3299
3300 // Actual rounding is needed along this path
3301
3302 // old_src holds the original input, needed for the case of src == dst
3303 FPURegister old_src = src;
3304 if (src == dst) {
3305 DCHECK(fpu_scratch != dst);
3306 Move(fpu_scratch, src);
3307 old_src = fpu_scratch;
3308 }
3309
3310 // Since only input whose real exponent value is less than kMantissaBits
3311 // (i.e., 23 or 52-bits) falls into this path, the value range of the input
3312 // falls into that of 23- or 53-bit integers. So we round the input to integer
3313 // values, then convert them back to floating-point.
3314 {
3315 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3316 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3317 fcvt_w_s(scratch, src, frm);
3318 fcvt_s_w(dst, scratch, frm);
3319 }
3320 // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3321 // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3322 // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3323 // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3324 // Therefore, we use sign-bit injection to produce +/-0 correctly. Instead of
3325 // testing for zero w/ a branch, we just insert sign-bit for everyone on this
3326 // path (this is where old_src is needed)
3327 fsgnj_s(dst, dst, old_src);
3328
3329 bind(&done);
3330}
3331#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3332// According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3333// the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3334// rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3335// round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3336// handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3337template <typename F>
3338void MacroAssembler::RoundHelper(VRegister dst, VRegister src, Register scratch,
3339 VRegister v_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm,
3340 bool keep_nan_same) {
3341 VU.set(scratch, std::is_same<F, float>::value ? E32 : E64, m1);
3342 // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3343 // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3344 // generating another branch)
3345
3346 // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3347 // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3348 // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3349 // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3350 // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3351 // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3352 // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3353 const int kFloatMantissaBits =
3354 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32MantissaBits : kFloat64MantissaBits;
3355 const int kFloatExponentBits =
3356 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBits : kFloat64ExponentBits;
3357 const int kFloatExponentBias =
3358 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBias : kFloat64ExponentBias;
3359
3360 // slli(rt, rs, 64 - (pos + size));
3361 // if (sign_extend) {
3362 // srai(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3363 // } else {
3364 // srli(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3365 // }
3366 vmv_vx(v_scratch, zero_reg);
3367 li(scratch, 64 - kFloatMantissaBits - kFloatExponentBits);
3368 vsll_vx(v_scratch, src, scratch);
3369 li(scratch, 64 - kFloatExponentBits);
3370 vsrl_vx(v_scratch, v_scratch, scratch);
3371 li(scratch, kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits);
3372 vmslt_vx(v0, v_scratch, scratch);
3373 VU.set(frm);
3374 vmv_vv(dst, src);
3375 if (dst == src) {
3376 vmv_vv(v_scratch, src);
3377 }
3378 vfcvt_x_f_v(dst, src, MaskType::Mask);
3379 vfcvt_f_x_v(dst, dst, MaskType::Mask);
3380
3381 // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3382 // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3383 // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3384 // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3385 if (dst == src) {
3386 vfsngj_vv(dst, dst, v_scratch);
3387 } else {
3388 vfsngj_vv(dst, dst, src);
3389 }
3390 if (!keep_nan_same) {
3391 vmfeq_vv(v0, src, src);
3392 vnot_vv(v0, v0);
3393 if (std::is_same<F, float>::value) {
3394 fmv_w_x(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3395 } else {
3396#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3397 fmv_d_x(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3398#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3399 fcvt_d_w(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3400#endif
3401 }
3402 vfadd_vf(dst, src, kScratchDoubleReg, MaskType::Mask);
3403 }
3404}

3646void MacroAssembler::InsertHighWordF64(FPURegister dst, Register src_high) {

3657 slli(scratch, scratch, 32);

3660 fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);

3696void MacroAssembler::LoadFPRImmediate(FPURegister dst, uint32_t src) {
3697 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3698 // Handle special values first.
3699 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f) && has_single_zero_reg_set_) {
3700 if (dst != kSingleRegZero) fmv_s(dst, kSingleRegZero);
3701 } else if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(-0.0f) &&
3702 has_single_zero_reg_set_) {
3703 Neg_s(dst, kSingleRegZero);
3704 } else {
3705 if (dst == kSingleRegZero) {
3706 DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f));
3707 fcvt_s_w(dst, zero_reg);
3708 has_single_zero_reg_set_ = true;
3709 } else {
3710 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f)) {
3711 fcvt_s_w(dst, zero_reg);
3712 } else {
3713 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3714 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3715 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(src)));
3716 fmv_w_x(dst, scratch);
3717 }
3718 }
3719 }
3720}
3721
3722void MacroAssembler::LoadFPRImmediate(FPURegister dst, uint64_t src) {
3723 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3724 // Handle special values first.
3725 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0) && has_double_zero_reg_set_) {
3726 if (dst != kDoubleRegZero) fmv_d(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
3727 } else if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(-0.0) &&
3728 has_double_zero_reg_set_) {
3729 Neg_d(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
3730 } else {
3731#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3732 if (dst == kDoubleRegZero) {
3733 DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0));
3734 fcvt_d_l(dst, zero_reg);
3735 has_double_zero_reg_set_ = true;
3736 } else {
3737 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3738 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3739 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0)) {
3740 fcvt_d_l(dst, zero_reg);
3741 } else {
3742 li(scratch, Operand(src));
3743 fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);
3744 }
3745 }
3746#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3747 if (dst == kDoubleRegZero) {
3748 DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0));
3749 fcvt_d_w(dst, zero_reg);
3750 has_double_zero_reg_set_ = true;
3751 } else {
3752 // Todo: need to clear the stack content?
3753 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0)) {
3754 fcvt_d_w(dst, zero_reg);
3755 } else {
3756 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3757 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3758 uint32_t low_32 = src & 0xffffffffull;
3759 uint32_t up_32 = src >> 32;
3760 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(-8));
3761 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(low_32)));
3762 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3763 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(up_32)));
3764 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
3765 LoadDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3766 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(8));
3767 }
3768 }
3769#endif
3770 }
3771}
3772
3773void MacroAssembler::CompareI(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
3774 Condition cond) {
3775 switch (cond) {
3776 case eq:
3777 Seq(rd, rs, rt);
3778 break;
3779 case ne:
3780 Sne(rd, rs, rt);
3781 break;
3782
3783 // Signed comparison.
3784 case greater:
3785 Sgt(rd, rs, rt);
3786 break;
3787 case greater_equal:
3788 Sge(rd, rs, rt); // rs >= rt
3789 break;
3790 case less:
3791 Slt(rd, rs, rt); // rs < rt
3792 break;
3793 case less_equal:
3794 Sle(rd, rs, rt); // rs <= rt
3795 break;
3796
3797 // Unsigned comparison.
3798 case Ugreater:
3799 Sgtu(rd, rs, rt); // rs > rt
3800 break;
3801 case Ugreater_equal:
3802 Sgeu(rd, rs, rt); // rs >= rt
3803 break;
3804 case Uless:
3805 Sltu(rd, rs, rt); // rs < rt
3806 break;
3807 case Uless_equal:
3808 Sleu(rd, rs, rt); // rs <= rt
3809 break;
3810 case cc_always:
3811 UNREACHABLE();
3812 default:
3813 UNREACHABLE();
3814 }
3815}

3818void MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfConditionNotZero(Register dest,
3819 Register condition) {

3822 seqz(scratch, condition);
3823 // neg + and may be more efficient than mul(dest, dest, scratch)
3824 neg(scratch, scratch); // 0 is still 0, 1 becomes all 1s
3825 and_(dest, dest, scratch);
3826}

3839void MacroAssembler::Clz32(Register rd, Register xx) {
3840 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
3841#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3842 clzw(rd, xx);
3843#else
3844 clz(rd, xx);
3845#endif
3846 } else {
3847 // 32 bit unsigned in lower word: count number of leading zeros.
3848 // int n = 32;
3849 // unsigned y;
3850
3851 // y = x >>16; if (y != 0) { n = n -16; x = y; }
3852 // y = x >> 8; if (y != 0) { n = n - 8; x = y; }
3853 // y = x >> 4; if (y != 0) { n = n - 4; x = y; }
3854 // y = x >> 2; if (y != 0) { n = n - 2; x = y; }
3855 // y = x >> 1; if (y != 0) {rd = n - 2; return;}
3856 // rd = n - x;
3857
3858 Label L0, L1, L2, L3, L4;
3859 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3860 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3861 Register x = rd;
3862 Register y = temps.Acquire();
3863 Register n = temps.Acquire();
3864 DCHECK(xx != y && xx != n);
3865 Move(x, xx);
3866 li(n, Operand(32));
3867#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3868 srliw(y, x, 16);
3869 BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3870 Move(x, y);
3871 addiw(n, n, -16);
3872 bind(&L0);
3873 srliw(y, x, 8);
3874 BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3875 addiw(n, n, -8);
3876 Move(x, y);
3877 bind(&L1);
3878 srliw(y, x, 4);
3879 BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3880 addiw(n, n, -4);
3881 Move(x, y);
3882 bind(&L2);
3883 srliw(y, x, 2);
3884 BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3885 addiw(n, n, -2);
3886 Move(x, y);
3887 bind(&L3);
3888 srliw(y, x, 1);
3889 subw(rd, n, x);
3890 BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3891 addiw(rd, n, -2);
3892 bind(&L4);
3893#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3894 srli(y, x, 16);
3895 BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3896 Move(x, y);
3897 addi(n, n, -16);
3898 bind(&L0);
3899 srli(y, x, 8);
3900 BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3901 addi(n, n, -8);
3902 Move(x, y);
3903 bind(&L1);
3904 srli(y, x, 4);
3905 BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3906 addi(n, n, -4);
3907 Move(x, y);
3908 bind(&L2);
3909 srli(y, x, 2);
3910 BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3911 addi(n, n, -2);
3912 Move(x, y);
3913 bind(&L3);
3914 srli(y, x, 1);
3915 sub(rd, n, x);
3916 BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3917 addi(rd, n, -2);
3918 bind(&L4);
3919#endif
3920 }
3921}

3923#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3924void MacroAssembler::Clz64(Register rd, Register xx) {
3925 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
3926 clz(rd, xx);
3927 } else {
3928 // 64 bit: count number of leading zeros.
3929 // int n = 64;
3930 // unsigned y;
3931
3932 // y = x >>32; if (y != 0) { n = n - 32; x = y; }
3933 // y = x >>16; if (y != 0) { n = n - 16; x = y; }
3934 // y = x >> 8; if (y != 0) { n = n - 8; x = y; }
3935 // y = x >> 4; if (y != 0) { n = n - 4; x = y; }
3936 // y = x >> 2; if (y != 0) { n = n - 2; x = y; }
3937 // y = x >> 1; if (y != 0) {rd = n - 2; return;}
3938 // rd = n - x;
3939
3940 Label L0, L1, L2, L3, L4, L5;
3941 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3942 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3943 Register x = rd;
3944 Register y = temps.Acquire();
3945 Register n = temps.Acquire();
3946 DCHECK(xx != y && xx != n);
3947 Move(x, xx);
3948 li(n, Operand(64));
3949 srli(y, x, 32);
3950 BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3951 addiw(n, n, -32);
3952 Move(x, y);
3953 bind(&L0);
3954 srli(y, x, 16);
3955 BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3956 addiw(n, n, -16);
3957 Move(x, y);
3958 bind(&L1);
3959 srli(y, x, 8);
3960 BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3961 addiw(n, n, -8);
3962 Move(x, y);
3963 bind(&L2);
3964 srli(y, x, 4);
3965 BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3966 addiw(n, n, -4);
3967 Move(x, y);
3968 bind(&L3);
3969 srli(y, x, 2);
3970 BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3971 addiw(n, n, -2);
3972 Move(x, y);
3973 bind(&L4);
3974 srli(y, x, 1);
3975 subw(rd, n, x);
3976 BranchShort(&L5, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
3977 addiw(rd, n, -2);
3978 bind(&L5);
3979 }
3980}

3982void MacroAssembler::Ctz32(Register rd, Register rs) {
3983 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
3984#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3985 ctzw(rd, rs);
3986#else
3987 ctz(rd, rs);
3988#endif
3989 } else {
3990 // Convert trailing zeroes to trailing ones, and bits to their left
3991 // to zeroes.
3992
3993 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3994 {
3995 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3996 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3997 AddWord(scratch, rs, -1);
3998 Xor(rd, scratch, rs);
3999 And(rd, rd, scratch);
4000 // Count number of leading zeroes.
4001 }
4002 Clz32(rd, rd);
4003 {
4004 // Subtract number of leading zeroes from 32 to get number of trailing
4005 // ones. Remember that the trailing ones were formerly trailing zeroes.
4006 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4007 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4008 li(scratch, 32);
4009 Sub32(rd, scratch, rd);
4010 }
4011 }
4012}
4013#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64

4015 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4016 ctz(rd, rs);
4017 } else {
4018 // Convert trailing zeroes to trailing ones, and bits to their left
4019 // to zeroes.
4020 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);

4024 AddWord(scratch, rs, -1);
4025 Xor(rd, scratch, rs);
4026 And(rd, rd, scratch);
4027 // Count number of leading zeroes.
4028 }
4029 Clz64(rd, rd);
4030 {
4031 // Subtract number of leading zeroes from 64 to get number of trailing
4032 // ones. Remember that the trailing ones were formerly trailing zeroes.
