4041void MacroAssembler::Popcnt32(Register rd, Register rs, Register scratch) {
4042 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4043#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4044 cpopw(rd, rs);
4045#else
4046 cpop(rd, rs);
4047#endif
4048 } else {
4049 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
4050 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
4051 // https://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#CountBitsSetParallel
4052 //
4053 // A generalization of the best bit counting method to integers of
4054 // bit-widths up to 128 (parameterized by type T) is this:
4055 //
4056 // v = v - ((v >> 1) & (T)~(T)0/3); // temp
4057 // v = (v & (T)~(T)0/15*3) + ((v >> 2) & (T)~(T)0/15*3); // temp
4058 // v = (v + (v >> 4)) & (T)~(T)0/255*15; // temp
4059 // c = (T)(v * ((T)~(T)0/255)) >> (sizeof(T) - 1) * BITS_PER_BYTE; //count
4060 //
4061 // There are algorithms which are faster in the cases where very few
4062 // bits are set but the algorithm here attempts to minimize the total
4063 // number of instructions executed even when a large number of bits
4064 // are set.
4065 // The number of instruction is 20.
4066 // uint32_t B0 = 0x55555555; // (T)~(T)0/3
4067 // uint32_t B1 = 0x33333333; // (T)~(T)0/15*3
4068 // uint32_t B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F; // (T)~(T)0/255*15
4069 // uint32_t value = 0x01010101; // (T)~(T)0/255
4070
4071 uint32_t shift = 24;
4072 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4073 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4074 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4075 Register value = temps.Acquire();
4076 DCHECK((rd != value) && (rs != value));
4077 li(value, 0x01010101); // value = 0x01010101;
4078 li(scratch2, 0x55555555); // B0 = 0x55555555;
4079 Srl32(scratch, rs, 1);
4080 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4081 Sub32(scratch, rs, scratch);
4082 li(scratch2, 0x33333333); // B1 = 0x33333333;
4083 slli(rd, scratch2, 4);
4084 or_(scratch2, scratch2, rd);
4085 And(rd, scratch, scratch2);
4086 Srl32(scratch, scratch, 2);
4087 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4088 Add32(scratch, rd, scratch);
4089 Srl32(rd, scratch, 4);
4090 Add32(rd, rd, scratch);
4091 li(scratch2, 0xF);
4092 Mul32(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F;
4093 And(rd, rd, scratch2);
4094 Mul32(rd, rd, value);
4095 Srl32(rd, rd, shift);
4096 }
4097}
4098
4099#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4100void MacroAssembler::Popcnt64(Register rd, Register rs, Register scratch) {
4101 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4102 cpop(rd, rs);
4103 } else {
4104 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
4105 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
4106 // uint64_t B0 = 0x5555555555555555l; // (T)~(T)0/3
4107 // uint64_t B1 = 0x3333333333333333l; // (T)~(T)0/15*3
4108 // uint64_t B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fl; // (T)~(T)0/255*15
4109 // uint64_t value = 0x0101010101010101l; // (T)~(T)0/255
4110 // uint64_t shift = 24; // (sizeof(T) - 1) * BITS_PER_BYTE
4111 uint64_t shift = 24;
4112 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4113 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4114 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4115 Register value = temps.Acquire();
4116 DCHECK((rd != value) && (rs != value));
4117 li(value, 0x1111111111111111l); // value = 0x1111111111111111l;
4118 li(scratch2, 5);
4119 Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B0 = 0x5555555555555555l;
4120 Srl64(scratch, rs, 1);
4121 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4122 SubWord(scratch, rs, scratch);
4123 li(scratch2, 3);
4124 Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B1 = 0x3333333333333333l;
4125 And(rd, scratch, scratch2);
4126 Srl64(scratch, scratch, 2);
4127 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4128 AddWord(scratch, rd, scratch);
4129 Srl64(rd, scratch, 4);
4130 AddWord(rd, rd, scratch);
4131 li(scratch2, 0xF);
4132 li(value, 0x0101010101010101l); // value = 0x0101010101010101l;
4133 Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fl;
4134 And(rd, rd, scratch2);
4135 Mul64(rd, rd, value);
4136 srli(rd, rd, 32 + shift);
4137 }
4138}
4139#endif
4140void MacroAssembler::TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(Register result,
4141 DoubleRegister double_input,
4142 Label* done) {
4143 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4144 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4145 // if scratch == 1, exception happens during truncation
4146 Trunc_w_d(result, double_input, scratch);
4147 // If we had no exceptions (i.e., scratch==1) we are done.
4148 Branch(done, eq, scratch, Operand(1));
4149}
4150
4151void MacroAssembler::TruncateDoubleToI(Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone,
4152 Register result,
4153 DoubleRegister double_input,
4154 StubCallMode stub_mode) {
4155 Label done;
4156
4157 TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(result, double_input, &done);
4158
4159 // If we fell through then inline version didn't succeed - call stub
4160 // instead.
4161 push(ra);
4162 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize)); // Put input on stack.
4163 fsd(double_input, sp, 0);
4164#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4165 if (stub_mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
4166 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kDoubleToI), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
4167#else
4168 // For balance.
4169 if (false) {
4170#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4171 } else {
4172 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kDoubleToI);
4173 }
4174 LoadWord(result, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4175
4176 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize));
4177 pop(ra);
4178
4179 bind(&done);
4180}

4215void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4216 const Operand& rt, Label::Distance distance) {
4217 if (L->is_bound()) {
4218 if (!BranchShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt)) {
4219 if (cond != cc_always) {
4220 Label skip;
4221 Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4222 BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4223 BranchLong(L);
4224 bind(&skip);
4225 } else {
4226 BranchLong(L);
4227 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4228 }
4229 }
4230 } else {
4231 if (is_trampoline_emitted() && distance == Label::Distance::kFar) {
4232 if (cond != cc_always) {
4233 Label skip;
4234 Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4235 BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4236 BranchLong(L);
4237 bind(&skip);
4238 } else {
4239 BranchLong(L);
4240 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4241 }
4242 } else {
4243 BranchShort(L, cond, rs, rt);
4244 }
4245 }

4248void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4249 RootIndex index, Label::Distance distance) {
4250 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4251 Register right = temps.Acquire();
4252 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4253 Register left = rs;
4254 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
4255 is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
4256 left = temps.Acquire();
4257 Sll32(left, rs, 0);
4258 }
4259 LoadTaggedRoot(right, index);
4260 Branch(L, cond, left, Operand(right));
4261 } else {
4262 LoadRoot(right, index);
4263 Branch(L, cond, rs, Operand(right));
4264 }

4267void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedAndBranch(Label* label, Condition cond,
4268 Register r1, const Operand& r2,
4269 bool need_link) {
4270 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4271 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);

4279 Sll32(scratch1, r2.rm(), 0);

4284 }
4285 } else {

4339
4340bool MacroAssembler::BranchShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L, Condition cond,
4341 Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4342 DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4343 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4344 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4345 Register scratch = no_reg;
4346 if (!rt.is_reg()) {
4347 if (rt.immediate() == 0) {
4348 scratch = zero_reg;
4349 } else {
4350 scratch = temps.Acquire();
4351 li(scratch, rt);
4352 }
4353 } else {
4354 scratch = rt.rm();
4355 }
4356 {
4357 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4358 switch (cond) {
4359 case cc_always:
4360 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4361 j(offset);
4362 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4363 break;
4364 case eq:
4365 // rs == rt
4366 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4367 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4368 j(offset);
4369 } else {
4370 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4371 beq(rs, scratch, offset);
4372 }
4373 break;
4374 case ne:
4375 // rs != rt
4376 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4377 break; // No code needs to be emitted
4378 } else {
4379 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4380 bne(rs, scratch, offset);
4381 }
4382 break;
4383
4384 // Signed comparison.
4385 case greater:
4386 // rs > rt
4387 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4388 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4389 } else {
4390 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4391 bgt(rs, scratch, offset);
4392 }
4393 break;
4394 case greater_equal:
4395 // rs >= rt
4396 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4397 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4398 j(offset);
4399 } else {
4400 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4401 bge(rs, scratch, offset);
4402 }
4403 break;
4404 case less:
4405 // rs < rt
4406 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4407 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4408 } else {
4409 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4410 blt(rs, scratch, offset);
4411 }
4412 break;
4413 case less_equal:
4414 // rs <= rt
4415 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4416 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4417 j(offset);
4418 } else {
4419 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4420 ble(rs, scratch, offset);
4421 }
4422 break;
4423
4424 // Unsigned comparison.
4425 case Ugreater:
4426 // rs > rt
4427 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4428 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4429 } else {
4430 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4431 bgtu(rs, scratch, offset);
4432 }
4433 break;
4434 case Ugreater_equal:
4435 // rs >= rt
4436 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4437 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4438 j(offset);
4439 } else {
4440 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4441 bgeu(rs, scratch, offset);
4442 }
4443 break;
4444 case Uless:
4445 // rs < rt
4446 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4447 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4448 } else {
4449 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4450 bltu(rs, scratch, offset);
4451 }
4452 break;
4453 case Uless_equal:
4454 // rs <= rt
4455 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4456 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4457 j(offset);
4458 } else {
4459 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4460 bleu(rs, scratch, offset);
4461 }
4462 break;
4463 default:
4464 UNREACHABLE();
4465 }
4466 }
4467
4468 CheckTrampolinePoolQuick(1);
4469 return true;
4470}

4560// Pre r6 we need to use a bgezal or bltzal, but they can't be used directly
4561// with the slt instructions. We could use sub or add instead but we would miss
4562// overflow cases, so we keep slt and add an intermediate third instruction.
4563bool MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L,
4564 Condition cond, Register rs,
4565 const Operand& rt) {
4566 DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4567 if (!is_near(L, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4568
4569 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4570 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4571 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4572
4573 if (cond == cc_always) {
4574 offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4575 jal(offset);
4576 } else {
4577 Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs,
4578 Operand(GetRtAsRegisterHelper(rt, scratch)));
4579 offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4580 jal(offset);
4581 }
4582
4583 return true;
4584}

4617MemOperand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4618 ExternalReference reference, Register scratch) {
4619 if (root_array_available_ && options().enable_root_relative_access) {
4620 int64_t offset =
4621 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4622 if (is_int32(offset)) {
4623 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4624 }
4625 }
4626 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
4627 if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
4628 // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
4629 // kRootRegister.
4630 intptr_t offset =
4631 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4632 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
4633 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4634 } else {
4635 // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
4636 DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4637 LoadWord(scratch,
4638 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4639 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
4640 isolate(), reference)));
4641 return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4642 }
4643 }
4644 DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4645 li(scratch, reference);
4646 return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4647}

4658void MacroAssembler::Jump(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
4659 const Operand& rt) {
4660 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4661 if (cond == cc_always) {
4662 jr(target);
4663 ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
4664 } else {

4666 Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4667 jr(target);
4668 }

4672 Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4673 Label skip;

4675 Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4676 }
4677 {
4678 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4679 li(t6, Operand(target, rmode));
4680 Jump(t6, al, zero_reg, Operand(zero_reg));
4681 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4682 bind(&skip);
4683 }

4692void MacroAssembler::Jump(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
4693 Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4694 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4695 DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
4696 Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
4697
4698 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
4699 if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
4700 // Inline the trampoline.
4701 Label skip;
4702 if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4703 TailCallBuiltin(builtin);
4704 bind(&skip);
4705 return;
4706 }
4707 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4708 if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
4709 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
4710 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
4711 Label skip;
4712 if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4713 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
4714 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4715 GenPCRelativeJump(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4716 bind(&skip);
4717 } else {
4718 Jump(code.address(), rmode, cond);
4719 }
4720}

4723 li(t6, reference);
4724 Jump(t6);
4725}

4731 if (cond == cc_always) {
4732 jalr(ra, target, 0);
4733 } else {
4734 BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4735 Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4736 jalr(ra, target, 0);
4737 }

4739
4740void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRootAndBranch(const Register& obj,
4741 RootIndex index, Condition cc,
4742 Label* target) {
4743 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4744 // AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(obj);
4745 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4746 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index)) {
4747 CompareTaggedAndBranch(target, cc, obj, Operand(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index)));
4748 return;
4749 }
4750 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
4751 DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
4752 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
4753 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
4754 DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
4755 LoadRoot(temp, index);
4756 CompareTaggedAndBranch(target, cc, obj, Operand(temp));
4757}
4758// Compare the object in a register to a value from the root list.
4759void MacroAssembler::CompareRootAndBranch(const Register& obj, RootIndex index,
4760 Condition cc, Label* target,
4761 ComparisonMode mode) {
4762 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4763 if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
4764 !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
4765 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
4766 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
4767 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4768 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
4769 DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
4770 LoadRoot(temp, index);
4771 Branch(target, cc, obj, Operand(temp));
4772 return;
4773 }
4774 CompareTaggedRootAndBranch(obj, index, cc, target);
4775}
4776
4777void MacroAssembler::JumpIfIsInRange(Register value, unsigned lower_limit,
4778 unsigned higher_limit,
4779 Label* on_in_range) {
4780 if (lower_limit != 0) {
4781 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4782 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4783 SubWord(scratch, value, Operand(lower_limit));
4784 Branch(on_in_range, Uless_equal, scratch,
4785 Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
4786 } else {
4787 Branch(on_in_range, Uless_equal, value,
4788 Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
4789 }
4790}

4792void MacroAssembler::Call(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode, Condition cond,
4793 Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4794 li(t6, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(target), rmode), ADDRESS_LOAD);
4795 Call(t6, cond, rs, rt);
4796}
4797
4798void MacroAssembler::Call(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
4799 Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4800 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4801 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4802 DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
4803 Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
4804
4805 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
4806 if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
4807 // Inline the trampoline.
4808 CHECK_EQ(cond, Condition::al); // Implement if necessary.
4809 CallBuiltin(builtin);
4810 return;
4811 }
4812
4813 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4814
4815 if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
4816 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
4817 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
4818 Label skip;
4819 if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4820 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
4821 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4822 GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4823 bind(&skip);
4824 } else {
4825 Call(code.address(), rmode);
4826 }
4827}

4829void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(Register builtin_index,
4830 Register target) {
4831#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4832 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 8);
4833#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
4834 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 4);
4835#endif
4836 static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1);
4837 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
4838
4839 // The builtin register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
4840 SmiUntag(target, builtin_index);
4841 CalcScaledAddress(target, kRootRegister, target, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
4842 LoadWord(target,
4843 MemOperand(target, IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset()));
4844}

4852void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
4853 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
4854 switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
4855 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
4856 li(t6, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
4857 Call(t6);
4858 break;
4859 }
4860 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
4861 near_call(static_cast<int>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
4862 break;
4863 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
4864 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
4865 Call(t6);
4866 break;
4867 }
4868 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
4869 if (options().use_pc_relative_calls_and_jumps_for_mksnapshot) {
4870 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
4871 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
4872 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
4873 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
4874 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4875 GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4876 } else {
4877 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
4878 Call(t6);
4879 }
4880 break;
4881 }
4882 }
4883}

4900 break;
4901 }
4902 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:

4904 break;
4905 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
4906 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);

4910 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {

4938void MacroAssembler::PatchAndJump(Address target) {
4939 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4940 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4941 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4942 auipc(scratch, 0); // Load PC into scratch
4943 LoadWord(t6, MemOperand(scratch, kInstrSize * 4));
4944 jr(t6);
4945 nop(); // For alignment
4946#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4947 DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(pc_) % 8, 0);
4948#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
4949 DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint32_t>(pc_) % 4, 0);
4950#endif
4951 *reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(pc_) = target; // pc_ should be align.
4952 pc_ += sizeof(uintptr_t);
4953}
4954
4955void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
4956 // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
4957 // once an exit frame has been constructed.
4958 //
4959 // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
4960 // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
4961 // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
4962 //
4963 // Compute the return address in lr to return to after the jump below. The
4964 // pc is already at '+ 8' from the current instruction; but return is after
4965 // three instructions, so add another 4 to pc to get the return address.
4966 //
4967 Assembler::BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4968 int kNumInstructionsToJump = 5;
4969 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension) kNumInstructionsToJump = 4;
4970 Label find_ra;
4971 // Adjust the value in ra to point to the correct return location, one
4972 // instruction past the real call into C code (the jalr(t6)), and push it.
4973 // This is the return address of the exit frame.
4974 auipc(ra, 0); // Set ra the current PC
4975 bind(&find_ra);
4976 addi(ra, ra,
4977 (kNumInstructionsToJump + 1) *
4978 kInstrSize); // Set ra to insn after the call
4979
4980 // This spot was reserved in EnterExitFrame.
4981 StoreWord(ra, MemOperand(sp));
4982 addi(sp, sp, -kCArgsSlotsSize);
4983 // Stack is still aligned.
4984
4985 // Call the C routine.
4986 Mv(t6,
4987 target); // Function pointer to t6 to conform to ABI for PIC.
4988 jalr(t6);
4989 // Make sure the stored 'ra' points to this position.
4990 DCHECK_EQ(kNumInstructionsToJump, InstructionsGeneratedSince(&find_ra));
4991}

4993void MacroAssembler::Ret(Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4994 Jump(ra, cond, rs, rt);
4995 if (cond == al) {
4996 ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
4997 }
4998}

5022void MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(int drop, Condition cond, Register r1,
5023 const Operand& r2) {

5025 Label skip;
5026 if (cond != cc_always) {
5027 Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), r1, r2);

5038void MacroAssembler::Drop(int count, Condition cond, Register reg,
5039 const Operand& op) {
5040 if (count <= 0) {
5041 return;
5042 }
5043
5044 Label skip;
5045
5046 if (cond != al) {
5047 Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), reg, op);
5048 }
5049
5050 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(count * kSystemPointerSize));
5051
5052 if (cond != al) {
5053 bind(&skip);
5054 }
5055}

5057void MacroAssembler::Swap(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register scratch) {
5058 if (scratch == no_reg) {
5059 Xor(reg1, reg1, Operand(reg2));
5060 Xor(reg2, reg2, Operand(reg1));
5061 Xor(reg1, reg1, Operand(reg2));
5062 } else {
5063 Mv(scratch, reg1);
5064 Mv(reg1, reg2);
5065 Mv(reg2, scratch);
5066 }
5067}

5069void MacroAssembler::Call(Label* target) { BranchAndLink(target); }
5070
5071void MacroAssembler::LoadAddress(Register dst, Label* target,
5072 RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
5073 int32_t offset;
5074 if (CalculateOffset(target, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset32)) {
5075 CHECK(is_int32(offset + 0x800));
5076 int32_t Hi20 = (((int32_t)offset + 0x800) >> 12);
5077 int32_t Lo12 = (int32_t)offset << 20 >> 20;
5078 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5079 auipc(dst, Hi20);
5080 addi(dst, dst, Lo12);
5081 } else {
5082 uintptr_t address = jump_address(target);
5083 li(dst, Operand(address, rmode), ADDRESS_LOAD);
5084 }
5085}

5093
5094void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size,
5095 PushArrayOrder order) {
5096 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5097 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5098 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5099 Label loop, entry;
5100 if (order == PushArrayOrder::kReverse) {
5101 Mv(scratch, zero_reg);
5102 jmp(&entry);
5103 bind(&loop);
5104 CalcScaledAddress(scratch2, array, scratch, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5105 LoadWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
5106 push(scratch2);
5107 AddWord(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
5108 bind(&entry);
5109 Branch(&loop, less, scratch, Operand(size));
5110 } else {
5111 Mv(scratch, size);
5112 jmp(&entry);
5113 bind(&loop);
5114 CalcScaledAddress(scratch2, array, scratch, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5115 LoadWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
5116 push(scratch2);
5117 bind(&entry);
5118 AddWord(scratch, scratch, Operand(-1));
5119 Branch(&loop, greater_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5120 }
5121}

5131// Exception handling.
5132
5133void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
5134 // Adjust this code if not the case.
5135 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
5136 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0 * kSystemPointerSize);
5137
5138 Push(Smi::zero()); // Padding.
5139
5140 // Link the current handler as the next handler.
5141 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5142 Register handler_address = temps.Acquire();
5143 li(handler_address,
5144 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
5145 Register handler = temps.Acquire();
5146 LoadWord(handler, MemOperand(handler_address));
5147 push(handler);
5148
5149 // Set this new handler as the current one.
5150 StoreWord(sp, MemOperand(handler_address));
5151}
5152
5153void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
5154 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
5155 pop(a1);
5156 AddWord(sp, sp,
5157 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(StackHandlerConstants::kSize -
5158 kSystemPointerSize)));
5159 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5160 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5161 li(scratch,
5162 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
5163 StoreWord(a1, MemOperand(scratch));
5164}

5166void MacroAssembler::FPUCanonicalizeNaN(const DoubleRegister dst,
5167 const DoubleRegister src) {
5168 // Subtracting 0.0 preserves all inputs except for signalling NaNs, which
5169 // become quiet NaNs. We use fsub rather than fadd because fsub preserves -0.0
5170 // inputs: -0.0 + 0.0 = 0.0, but -0.0 - 0.0 = -0.0.
5171 if (!IsDoubleZeroRegSet()) {
5172 LoadFPRImmediate(kDoubleRegZero, 0.0);
5173 }
5174 fsub_d(dst, src, kDoubleRegZero);
5175}

5213
5214void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(Register num_args, Register scratch1,
5215 Register scratch2,
5216 Label* stack_overflow, Label* done) {
5217 // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
5218 // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
5219 // limit" is checked.
5220 DCHECK(stack_overflow != nullptr || done != nullptr);
5221 LoadStackLimit(scratch1, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
5222 // Make scratch1 the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
5223 // here which will cause scratch1 to become negative.
5224 SubWord(scratch1, sp, scratch1);
5225 // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
5226 SllWord(scratch2, num_args, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5227 // Signed comparison.
5228 if (stack_overflow != nullptr) {
5229 Branch(stack_overflow, le, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
5230 } else if (done != nullptr) {
5231 Branch(done, gt, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
5232 } else {
5233 UNREACHABLE();
5234 }
5235}
5236
5237void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
5238 Register actual_parameter_count,
5239 Label* done, InvokeType type) {
5240 Label regular_invoke;
5241
5242 // a0: actual arguments count
5243 // a1: function (passed through to callee)
5244 // a2: expected arguments count
5245
5246 DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, a0);
5247 DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, a2);
5248
5249 // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
5250 // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
5251 SubWord(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
5252 actual_parameter_count);
5253 Branch(&regular_invoke, le, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5254
5255 Label stack_overflow;
5256 {
5257 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5258 StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, temps.Acquire(),
5259 temps.Acquire(), &stack_overflow);
5260 }
5261 // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
5262 // receiver and the return address.
5263 {
5264 Label copy;
5265 Register src = a6, dest = a7;
5266 Move(src, sp);
5267 SllWord(t0, expected_parameter_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5268 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(t0));
5269 // Update stack pointer.
5270 Move(dest, sp);
5271 Move(t0, actual_parameter_count);
5272 bind(&copy);
5273 LoadWord(t1, MemOperand(src, 0));
5274 StoreWord(t1, MemOperand(dest, 0));
5275 SubWord(t0, t0, Operand(1));
5276 AddWord(src, src, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5277 AddWord(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5278 Branch(&copy, gt, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5279 }
5280
5281 // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
5282 LoadRoot(t0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5283 {
5284 Label loop;
5285 bind(&loop);
5286 StoreWord(t0, MemOperand(a7, 0));
5287 SubWord(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
5288 AddWord(a7, a7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5289 Branch(&loop, gt, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5290 }
5291 Branch(&regular_invoke);
5292
5293 bind(&stack_overflow);
5294 {
5295 FrameScope frame(
5296 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5297 CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
5298 break_(0xCC);
5299 }
5300 bind(&regular_invoke);
5301}
5302
5303void MacroAssembler::CheckDebugHook(Register fun, Register new_target,
5304 Register expected_parameter_count,
5305 Register actual_parameter_count) {
5306 Label skip_hook;
5307 {
5308 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5309 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5310 li(scratch,
5311 ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5312 Lb(scratch, MemOperand(scratch));
5313 Branch(&skip_hook, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5314 }
5315 {
5316 // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
5317 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5318 Register receiver = temps.Acquire();
5319 LoadReceiver(receiver);
5320
5321 FrameScope frame(
5322 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5323 SmiTag(expected_parameter_count);
5324 Push(expected_parameter_count);
5325
5326 SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
5327 Push(actual_parameter_count);
5328
5329 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5330 Push(new_target);
5331 }
5332 Push(fun);
5333 Push(fun);
5334 Push(receiver);
5335 CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
5336 Pop(fun);
5337 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5338 Pop(new_target);
5339 }
5340
5341 Pop(actual_parameter_count);
5342 SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
5343
5344 Pop(expected_parameter_count);
5345 SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count);
5346 }
5347 bind(&skip_hook);
5348}
5349
5350void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
5351 Register expected_parameter_count,
5352 Register actual_parameter_count,
5353 InvokeType type) {
5354 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5355 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5356 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5357 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5358
5359 // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5360 CheckDebugHook(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5361 actual_parameter_count);
5362
5363 // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5364 if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5365 LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5366 }
5367
5368 Label done;
5369 InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, &done, type);
5370 // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5371 // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5372 // call sites.
5373 switch (type) {
5374 case InvokeType::kCall:
5375 CallJSFunction(function);
5376 break;
5377 case InvokeType::kJump:
5378 JumpJSFunction(function);
5379 break;
5380 }
5381
5382 // Continue here if InvokePrologue does handle the invocation due to
5383 // mismatched parameter counts.
5384 bind(&done);
5385}
5386
5387void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
5388 Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5389 InvokeType type) {
5390 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5391 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5392
5393 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5394 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5395 Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
5396 {
5397 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5398 Register temp_reg = temps.Acquire();
5399 LoadTaggedField(
5400 temp_reg,
5401 FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
5402 LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5403 // The argument count is stored as uint16_t
5404 Lhu(expected_parameter_count,
5405 FieldMemOperand(temp_reg,
5406 SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
5407 }
5408 InvokeFunctionCode(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5409 actual_parameter_count, type);
5410}
5411
5412void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function,
5413 Register expected_parameter_count,
5414 Register actual_parameter_count,
5415 InvokeType type) {
5416 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5417 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5418
5419 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5420 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5421
5422 // Get the function and setup the context.
5423 LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5424
5425 InvokeFunctionCode(a1, no_reg, expected_parameter_count,
5426 actual_parameter_count, type);
5427}

5528void MacroAssembler::LoadLane(int ts, VRegister dst, uint8_t laneidx,
5529 MemOperand src) {
5530 if (ts == 8) {
5531 Lbu(kScratchReg2, src);
5532 VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
5533 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5534 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5535 VU.set(kScratchReg, E8, m1);
5536 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5537 } else if (ts == 16) {
5538 Lhu(kScratchReg2, src);
5539 VU.set(kScratchReg, E16, m1);
5540 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5541 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5542 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5543 } else if (ts == 32) {
5544 Load32U(kScratchReg2, src);
5545 VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
5546 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5547 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5548 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5549 } else if (ts == 64) {
5550#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5551 LoadWord(kScratchReg2, src);
5552 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5553 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5554 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5555 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5556#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5557 LoadDouble(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
5558 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5559 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5560 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5561 vfmerge_vf(dst, kScratchDoubleReg, dst);
5562#endif
5563 } else {
5564 UNREACHABLE();
5565 }
5566}
5567
5568void MacroAssembler::StoreLane(int sz, VRegister src, uint8_t laneidx,
5569 MemOperand dst) {
5570 if (sz == 8) {
5571 VU.set(kScratchReg, E8, m1);
5572 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5573 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5574 Sb(kScratchReg, dst);
5575 } else if (sz == 16) {
5576 VU.set(kScratchReg, E16, m1);
5577 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5578 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5579 Sh(kScratchReg, dst);
5580 } else if (sz == 32) {
5581 VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
5582 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5583 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5584 Sw(kScratchReg, dst);
5585 } else {
5586 DCHECK_EQ(sz, 64);
5587 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5588 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5589#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5590 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5591 StoreWord(kScratchReg, dst);
5592#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5593 vfmv_fs(kScratchDoubleReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5594 StoreDouble(kScratchDoubleReg, dst);
5595#endif
5596 }

5600#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5601void MacroAssembler::AddOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
5602 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5603 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5604 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5605 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5606 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5607 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5608 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5609 li(scratch, Operand(right));
5610 right_reg = scratch;
5611 } else {
5612 right_reg = right.rm();
5613 }
5614 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
5615 overflow != scratch2);
5616 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5617 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5618 add(scratch2, left, right_reg);
5619 xor_(overflow, scratch2, left);
5620 xor_(scratch, scratch2, right_reg);
5621 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5622 Mv(dst, scratch2);
5623 } else {
5624 add(dst, left, right_reg);
5625 xor_(overflow, dst, left);
5626 xor_(scratch, dst, right_reg);
5627 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5628 }
5629}

5631void MacroAssembler::SubOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
5632 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5633 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5634 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5635 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5636 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5637 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5638 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5639 li(scratch, Operand(right));
5640 right_reg = scratch;
5641 } else {
5642 right_reg = right.rm();
5643 }
5644
5645 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
5646 overflow != scratch2);
5647 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5648
5649 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5650 sub(scratch2, left, right_reg);
5651 xor_(overflow, left, scratch2);
5652 xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
5653 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5654 Mv(dst, scratch2);
5655 } else {
5656 sub(dst, left, right_reg);
5657 xor_(overflow, left, dst);
5658 xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
5659 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5660 }
5661}

5663void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
5664 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5665 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5666 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5667 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5668 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5669 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5670 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5671 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5672 li(scratch, Operand(right));
5673 right_reg = scratch;
5674 } else {
5675 right_reg = right.rm();
5676 }
5677
5678 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
5679 overflow != scratch2);
5680 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5681 sext_w(overflow, left);
5682 sext_w(scratch2, right_reg);
5683
5684 mul(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
5685 sext_w(dst, overflow);
5686 xor_(overflow, overflow, dst);
5687}
5688
5689void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
5690 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5691 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5692 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5693 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5694 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5695 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5696 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5697 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5698 li(scratch, Operand(right));
5699 right_reg = scratch;
5700 } else {
5701 right_reg = right.rm();
5702 }
5703
5704 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
5705 overflow != scratch2);
5706 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5707 // use this sequence of "mulh/mul" according to recommendation of ISA Spec 7.1
5708 // upper part
5709 mulh(scratch2, left, right_reg);
5710 // lower part
5711 mul(dst, left, right_reg);
5712 // expand the sign of the lower part to 64bit
5713 srai(overflow, dst, 63);
5714 // if the upper part is not eqaul to the expanded sign bit of the lower part,
5715 // overflow happens
5716 xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
5717}

5807void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
5808 int num_arguments) {
5809 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5810 // All parameters are on the stack. a0 has the return value after call.
5811
5812 // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
5813 // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
5814 // expectation.
5815 CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
5816
5817 // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
5818 // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
5819 // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
5820 // smarter.
5821 PrepareCEntryArgs(num_arguments);
5822 PrepareCEntryFunction(ExternalReference::Create(f));
5823#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5824 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size));
5825#else
5826 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(1));
5827#endif
5828}
5829
5830void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
5831 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5832 const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
5833 DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
5834 if (function->nargs >= 0) {
5835 PrepareCEntryArgs(function->nargs);
5836 }
5837 JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
5838}
5839
5840void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
5841 bool builtin_exit_frame) {
5842 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5843 PrepareCEntryFunction(builtin);
5844 TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
5845}

5855void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
5856 Register scratch1,
5857 Register scratch2) {
5858 DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
5859 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
5860 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5861 // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
5862 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t
5863 // dummy_stats_counter_ field.
5864 li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
5865 Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5866 Add32(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
5867 Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5868 }
5869}

5871void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
5872 Register scratch1,
5873 Register scratch2) {

5876 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);

5878 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t
5879 // dummy_stats_counter_ field.
5880 li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));

5897
5898void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
5899 Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
5900 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
5901
5902 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5903 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
5904 Label ok;
5905
5906 JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
5907
5908 GetObjectType(object, map_tmp, tmp);
5909
5910 Branch(&ok, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, tmp, Operand(LAST_NAME_TYPE));
5911
5912 Branch(&ok, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, tmp, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
5913
5914 Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
5915
5916 Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
5917
5918 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5919
5920 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5921
5922 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
5923
5924 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
5925
5926 Abort(abort_reason);
5927 bind(&ok);
5928}
5929
5930void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
5931 Operand rt) {
5932 Label L;
5933 BranchShort(&L, cc, rs, rt);
5934 Abort(reason);
5935 // Will not return here.
5936 bind(&L);
5937}
5938
5939void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
5940 Label abort_start;
5941 bind(&abort_start);
5942 if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
5943 const char* msg = GetAbortReason(reason);
5944 RecordComment("Abort message: ");
5945 RecordComment(msg);
5946 }
5947
5948 // Avoid emitting call to builtin if requested.
5949 if (trap_on_abort()) {
5950 ebreak();
5951 return;
5952 }
5953
5954 if (should_abort_hard()) {
5955 // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
5956 FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
5957 PrepareCallCFunction(0, a0);
5958 li(a0, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(reason)));
5959 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::abort_with_reason(), 1);
5960 return;
5961 }
5962
5963 Move(a0, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
5964
5965 {
5966 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
5967 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
5968 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
5969 if (root_array_available()) {
5970 // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
5971 // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
5972 // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
5973 // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
5974 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, t6);
5975 Call(t6);
5976 } else {
5977 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
5978 }
5979 }
5980 // Will not return here.
5981 if (is_trampoline_pool_blocked()) {
5982 // If the calling code cares about the exact number of
5983 // instructions generated, we insert padding here to keep the size
5984 // of the Abort macro constant.
5985 // Currently in debug mode with debug_code enabled the number of
5986 // generated instructions is 10, so we use this as a maximum value.
5987 static const int kExpectedAbortInstructions = 10;
5988 int abort_instructions = InstructionsGeneratedSince(&abort_start);
5989 DCHECK_LE(abort_instructions, kExpectedAbortInstructions);
5990 while (abort_instructions++ < kExpectedAbortInstructions) {
5991 nop();
5992 }
5993 }
5994}

6042void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
6043 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6044 addi(sp, fp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);

6048
6049void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(int stack_space,
6050 StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
6051 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6052 DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
6053 frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
6054 frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
6055
6056 // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
6057 static_assert(2 * kSystemPointerSize ==
6058 ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
6059 static_assert(1 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
6060 static_assert(0 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
6061
6062 // This is how the stack will look:
6063 // fp + 2 (==kCallerSPDisplacement) - old stack's end
6064 // [fp + 1 (==kCallerPCOffset)] - saved old ra
6065 // [fp + 0 (==kCallerFPOffset)] - saved old fp
6066 // [fp - 1 StackFrame::EXIT Smi
6067 // [fp - 2 (==kSPOffset)] - sp of the called function
6068 // fp - (2 + stack_space + alignment) == sp == [fp - kSPOffset] - top of the
6069 // new stack (will contain saved ra)
6070
6071 // Save registers and reserve room for saved entry sp.
6072 addi(sp, sp,
6073 -2 * kSystemPointerSize - ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
6074 StoreWord(ra, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize));
6075 StoreWord(fp, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize));
6076 {
6077 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6078 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6079 li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
6080 StoreWord(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
6081 }
6082 // Set up new frame pointer.
6083 addi(fp, sp, ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
6084
6085 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6086 StoreWord(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
6087 }
6088
6089 {
6090 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6091 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6092 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6093 // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
6094 li(scratch, ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress,
6095 isolate()));
6096 StoreWord(fp, MemOperand(scratch));
6097 li(scratch,
6098 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate()));
6099 StoreWord(cp, MemOperand(scratch));
6100 }
6101
6102 const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6103
6104 // Reserve place for the return address, stack space and an optional slot
6105 // (used by DirectCEntry to hold the return value if a struct is
6106 // returned) and align the frame preparing for calling the runtime function.
6107 DCHECK_GE(stack_space, 0);
6108 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand((stack_space + 2) * kSystemPointerSize));
6109 if (frame_alignment > 0) {
6110 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6111 And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment)); // Align stack.
6112 }
6113
6114 // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
6115 // location.
6116 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6117 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6118 addi(scratch, sp, kSystemPointerSize);
6119 StoreWord(scratch, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
6120}
6121
6122void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register argument_count, bool do_return,
6123 bool argument_count_is_length) {
6124 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6125 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6126 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6127 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6128
6129 // Clear top frame.
6130 li(scratch,
6131 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate()));
6132 StoreWord(zero_reg, MemOperand(scratch));
6133
6134 // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
6135 li(scratch,
6136 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate()));
6137 LoadWord(cp, MemOperand(scratch));
6138
6139 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6140 UseScratchRegisterScope temp(this);
6141 Register scratch2 = temp.Acquire();
6142 li(scratch2, Operand(Context::kInvalidContext));
6143 StoreWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch));
6144 }
6145
6146 // Pop the arguments, restore registers, and return.
6147 Mv(sp, fp); // Respect ABI stack constraint.
6148 LoadWord(fp, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
6149 LoadWord(ra, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
6150
6151 if (argument_count.is_valid()) {
6152 if (argument_count_is_length) {
6153 add(sp, sp, argument_count);
6154 } else {
6155 CalcScaledAddress(sp, sp, argument_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
6156 }
6157 }
6158
6159 addi(sp, sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
6160
6161 if (do_return) {
6162 Ret();
6163 }
6164}
6165
6166int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
6167#if V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6168 // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
6169 // environment.
6170 // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one RISC-V
6171 // platform for another RISC-V platform with a different alignment.
6172 return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6173#else // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6174 // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
6175 // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
6176 // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
6177 // flag.
6178 return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
6179#endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6180}

6182void MacroAssembler::AssertStackIsAligned() {
6183 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6184 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6185 const int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
6186 const int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
6187
6188 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
6189 Label alignment_as_expected;
6190 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6191 {
6192 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6193 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6194 andi(scratch, sp, frame_alignment_mask);
6195 BranchShort(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6196 }
6197 // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort re-entering here.
6198 ebreak();
6199 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
6200 }
6201 }

6259void MacroAssembler::JumpIfObjectType(Label* target, Condition cc,
6260 Register object,
6261 InstanceType instance_type,
6262 Register scratch) {
6263 DCHECK(cc == eq || cc == ne);
6264 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6265 if (scratch == no_reg) {
6266 scratch = temps.Acquire();
6267 }
6268 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
6269 if (base::Optional<RootIndex> expected =
6270 InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(instance_type)) {
6271 Tagged_t ptr = ReadOnlyRootPtr(*expected);
6272 LoadCompressedMap(scratch, object);
6273 Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(ptr));
6274 return;
6275 }
6276 }
6277 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6278 Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(instance_type));
6279}
6280
6281void MacroAssembler::JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Register heap_object,
6282 Register scratch, Label* target,
6283 Label::Distance distance,
6284 Condition cc) {
6285 CHECK(cc == Condition::kUnsignedLessThan ||
6286 cc == Condition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual);
6287 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
6288#ifdef DEBUG
6289 Label ok;
6290 LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
6291 GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, scratch);
6292 Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
6293 Operand(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE - FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6294
6295 LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
6296 GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE,
6297 scratch);
6298 Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
6299 Operand(LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE -
6300 FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE));
6301
6302 Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidReceiver);
6303 bind(&ok);
6304#endif // DEBUG
6305
6306 // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
6307 // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
6308 // addresses.
6309 LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
6310 Branch(target, cc, scratch,
6311 Operand(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit));
6312 } else {
6313 static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
6314 GetObjectType(heap_object, scratch, scratch);
6315 Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6316 }
6317}

6440
6441template <typename F_TYPE>
6442void MacroAssembler::FloatMinMaxHelper(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
6443 FPURegister src2, MaxMinKind kind) {
6444 DCHECK((std::is_same<F_TYPE, float>::value) ||
6445 (std::is_same<F_TYPE, double>::value));
6446
6447 if (src1 == src2 && dst != src1) {
6448 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6449 fmv_s(dst, src1);
6450 } else {
6451 fmv_d(dst, src1);
6452 }
6453 return;
6454 }
6455
6456 Label done, nan;
6457
6458 // For RISCV, fmin_s returns the other non-NaN operand as result if only one
6459 // operand is NaN; but for JS, if any operand is NaN, result is Nan. The
6460 // following handles the discrepency between handling of NaN between ISA and
6461 // JS semantics
6462 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6463 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6464 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6465 CompareIsNotNanF32(scratch, src1, src2);
6466 } else {
6467 CompareIsNotNanF64(scratch, src1, src2);
6468 }
6469 BranchFalseF(scratch, &nan);
6470
6471 if (kind == MaxMinKind::kMax) {
6472 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6473 fmax_s(dst, src1, src2);
6474 } else {
6475 fmax_d(dst, src1, src2);
6476 }
6477 } else {
6478 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6479 fmin_s(dst, src1, src2);
6480 } else {
6481 fmin_d(dst, src1, src2);
6482 }
6483 }
6484 j(&done);
6485
6486 bind(&nan);
6487 // if any operand is NaN, return NaN (fadd returns NaN if any operand is NaN)
6488 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6489 fadd_s(dst, src1, src2);
6490 } else {
6491 fadd_d(dst, src1, src2);
6492 }
6493
6494 bind(&done);
6495}
6496
6497void MacroAssembler::Float32Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
6498 FPURegister src2) {
6499 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6500 FloatMinMaxHelper<float>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMax);
6501}
6502
6503void MacroAssembler::Float32Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
6504 FPURegister src2) {
6505 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6506 FloatMinMaxHelper<float>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMin);
6507}
6508
6509void MacroAssembler::Float64Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
6510 FPURegister src2) {
6511 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6512 FloatMinMaxHelper<double>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMax);
6513}
6514
6515void MacroAssembler::Float64Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
6516 FPURegister src2) {

6520
6521int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedDWords(int num_gp_arguments,
6522 int num_fp_arguments) {
6523 int stack_passed_dwords = 0;
6524
6525 // Up to eight integer arguments are passed in registers a0..a7 and
6526 // up to eight floating point arguments are passed in registers fa0..fa7
6527 if (num_gp_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
6528 stack_passed_dwords += num_gp_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
6529 }
6530 if (num_fp_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
6531 stack_passed_dwords += num_fp_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
6532 }
6533 stack_passed_dwords += kCArgSlotCount;
6534 return stack_passed_dwords;
6535}
6536
6537void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
6538 int num_double_arguments,
6539 Register scratch) {
6540 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6541 int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
6542
6543 // Up to eight simple arguments in a0..a7, fa0..fa7.
6544 // Remaining arguments are pushed on the stack (arg slot calculation handled
6545 // by CalculateStackPassedDWords()).
6546 int stack_passed_arguments =
6547 CalculateStackPassedDWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
6548 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
6549 // Make stack end at alignment and make room for stack arguments and the
6550 // original value of sp.
6551 Mv(scratch, sp);
6552 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand((stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
6553 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6554 And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment));
6555 StoreWord(scratch,
6556 MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
6557 } else {
6558 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
6559 }
6560}
6561
6562void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
6563 Register scratch) {
6564 PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
6565}
6566
6567int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function,
6568 int num_reg_arguments,
6569 int num_double_arguments,

6575 set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
6576}

6599
6600int MacroAssembler::CallCFunctionHelper(
6601 Register function, int num_reg_arguments, int num_double_arguments,
6602 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots, Label* return_location) {
6603 DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
6604 DCHECK(has_frame());
6605 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6606 // Make sure that the stack is aligned before calling a C function unless
6607 // running in the simulator. The simulator has its own alignment check which
6608 // provides more information.
6609 // The argument stots are presumed to have been set up by
6610 // PrepareCallCFunction.
6611
6612#if V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6613 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6614 int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6615 int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
6616 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
6617 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6618 Label alignment_as_expected;
6619 {
6620 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6621 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6622 And(scratch, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
6623 BranchShort(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6624 }
6625 // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort possibly
6626 // re-entering here.
6627 ebreak();
6628 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
6629 }
6630 }
6631#endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6632
6633 // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
6634 // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
6635 // stays correct.
6636 Label get_pc;
6637 {
6638 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
6639 if (function != t6) {
6640 Mv(t6, function);
6641 function = t6;
6642 }
6643
6644 // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains
6645 // iterable, even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS
6646 // and C frames.
6647 // 't' registers are caller-saved so this is safe as a scratch register.
6648 Register pc_scratch = t1;
6649 Register scratch = t2;
6650
6651 LoadAddress(pc_scratch, &get_pc);
6652 // See x64 code for reasoning about how to address the isolate data
6653 // fields.
6654 if (root_array_available()) {
6655 StoreWord(pc_scratch,
6656 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
6657 IsolateData::fast_c_call_caller_pc_offset()));
6658 StoreWord(fp, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
6659 IsolateData::fast_c_call_caller_fp_offset()));
6660 } else {
6661 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate());
6662 li(scratch,
6663 ExternalReference::fast_c_call_caller_pc_address(isolate()));
6664 StoreWord(pc_scratch, MemOperand(scratch));
6665 li(scratch,
6666 ExternalReference::fast_c_call_caller_fp_address(isolate()));
6667 StoreWord(fp, MemOperand(scratch));
6668 }
6669 }
6670 }
6671
6672 Call(function);
6673 int call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
6674 bind(&get_pc);
6675 if (return_location) bind(return_location);
6676
6677 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
6678 // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
6679 if (root_array_available()) {
6680 StoreWord(zero_reg,
6681 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
6682 IsolateData::fast_c_call_caller_fp_offset()));
6683 } else {
6684 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate());
6685 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6686 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6687 li(scratch, ExternalReference::fast_c_call_caller_fp_address(isolate()));
6688 StoreWord(zero_reg, MemOperand(scratch));
6689 }
6690 }
6691
6692 int stack_passed_arguments =
6693 CalculateStackPassedDWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
6694
6695 if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
6696 LoadWord(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
6697 } else {
6698 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
6699 }
6700
6701 return call_pc_offset;
6702}

6706void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, int mask, Condition cc,
6707 Label* condition_met) {
6708 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6709 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6710 temps.Include(t6);
6711 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6712 And(scratch, object, Operand(~MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
6713 LoadWord(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunkLayout::kFlagsOffset));
6714 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(mask));
6715 Branch(condition_met, cc, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6716}

6718Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
6719 Register reg4, Register reg5,
6720 Register reg6) {
6721 RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
6722
6723 const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
6724 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
6725 int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
6726 Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
6727 if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
6728 return candidate;
6729 }
6730 UNREACHABLE();
6731}

6794void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object) {
6795 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6796 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
6797#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
6798 // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
6799 // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
6800 // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
6801 LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
6802 code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
6803 kJSEntrypointTag);
6804 Call(code);
6805#else
6806 LoadTaggedField(code,
6807 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6808 CallCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag);
6809#endif
6810}

6812void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
6813 JumpMode jump_mode) {
6814 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6815 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
6816#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
6817 // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
6818 // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
6819 // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
6820 LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
6821 code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
6822 kJSEntrypointTag);
6823 DCHECK_EQ(jump_mode, JumpMode::kJump);
6824 // We jump through x17 here because for Branch Identification (BTI) we use
6825 // "Call" (`bti c`) rather than "Jump" (`bti j`) landing pads for tail-called
6826 // code. See TailCallBuiltin for more information.
6827 DCHECK_NE(code, t6);
6828 mv(t6, code);
6829 Jump(t6);
6830#else
6831 LoadTaggedField(code,
6832 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6833 JumpCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
6834#endif
6835}

6948void MacroAssembler::DropArguments(Register count, ArgumentsCountType type,
6949 ArgumentsCountMode mode, Register scratch) {
6950 switch (type) {
6951 case kCountIsInteger: {
6952 CalcScaledAddress(sp, sp, count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
6953 break;
6954 }
6955 case kCountIsSmi: {
6956 static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1 && kSmiTag == 0);
6957 DCHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg);
6958 SmiScale(scratch, count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
6959 AddWord(sp, sp, scratch);
6960 break;
6961 }
6962 case kCountIsBytes: {
6963 AddWord(sp, sp, count);
6964 break;
6965 }
6966 }
6967 if (mode == kCountExcludesReceiver) {
6968 AddWord(sp, sp, kSystemPointerSize);
6969 }
6970}
6971
6972void MacroAssembler::DropArgumentsAndPushNewReceiver(Register argc,
6973 Register receiver,
6974 ArgumentsCountType type,
6975 ArgumentsCountMode mode,
6976 Register scratch) {
6977 DCHECK(!AreAliased(argc, receiver));
6978 if (mode == kCountExcludesReceiver) {
6979 // Drop arguments without receiver and override old receiver.
6980 DropArguments(argc, type, kCountIncludesReceiver, scratch);
6981 StoreWord(receiver, MemOperand(sp));
6982 } else {
6983 DropArguments(argc, type, mode, scratch);
6984 push(receiver);
6985 }
6986}
6987
6988// Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
6989// from handle and propagates exceptions. Restores context. On return removes
6990// *stack_space_operand * kSystemPointerSize or stack_space * kSystemPointerSize
6991// (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
6992// allocated for the fast call).
6993void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
6994 Register function_address,
6995 ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
6996 int stack_space, MemOperand* stack_space_operand,
6997 MemOperand return_value_operand) {
6998 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
6999 using ER = ExternalReference;
7000
7001 Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
7002 MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7003 ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
7004 MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7005 ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
7006 MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7007 ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
7008
7009 Register return_value = a0;
7010 Register scratch = a4;
7011 Register scratch2 = a5;
7012
7013 // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
7014 // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
7015 // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
7016 Register prev_next_address_reg = kScratchReg;
7017 Register prev_limit_reg = s1;
7018 Register prev_level_reg = s2;
7019
7020 // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
7021 // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
7022 // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
7023 // call).
7024 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
7025 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7026 // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
7027 // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
7028 // fine).
7029 DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
7030 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7031 DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
7032 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7033 {
7034 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
7035 "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
7036 __ LoadWord(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
7037 __ LoadWord(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
7038 __ Lw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
7039 __ Add32(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
7040 __ Sw(scratch, level_mem_op);
7041 }
7042
7043 Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
7044 if (with_profiling) {
7045 __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
7046 __ Lb(scratch, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7047 ER::execution_mode_address(isolate), no_reg));
7048 __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
7049 Operand(zero_reg));
7050#ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
7051 __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
7052 __ li(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
7053 __ Lw(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
7054 __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
7055 Operand(zero_reg));
7056#endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
7057 }
7058
7059 __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
7060 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
7061 __ bind(&done_api_call);
7062
7063 Label propagate_exception;
7064 Label delete_allocated_handles;
7065 Label leave_exit_frame;
7066
7067 __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
7068 __ LoadWord(return_value, return_value_operand);
7069
7070 {
7071 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
7072 masm,
7073 "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
7074 "Restore previous handle scope.");
7075 __ StoreWord(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
7076 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7077 __ Lw(scratch, level_mem_op);
7078 __ Sub32(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
7079 __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall, scratch,
7080 Operand(prev_level_reg));
7081 }
7082 __ Sw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
7083 __ LoadWord(scratch, limit_mem_op);
7084 __ Branch(&delete_allocated_handles, ne, prev_limit_reg, Operand(scratch));
7085 }
7086 __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
7087 __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
7088
7089 Register stack_space_reg = prev_limit_reg;
7090 if (stack_space_operand == nullptr) {
7091 DCHECK_NE(stack_space, 0);
7092 __ li(stack_space_reg, Operand(stack_space));
7093 } else {
7094 DCHECK_EQ(stack_space, 0);
7095 static_assert(kCArgSlotCount == 0);
7096 __ LoadWord(stack_space_reg, *stack_space_operand);
7097 }
7098
7099 static constexpr bool kRegisterContainsSlotCount = false;
7100 __ LeaveExitFrame(stack_space_reg, NO_EMIT_RETURN,
7101 kRegisterContainsSlotCount);
7102
7103 {
7104 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
7105 "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
7106 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
7107 __ LoadWord(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7108 ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
7109 __ Branch(&propagate_exception, ne, scratch, Operand(scratch2));
7110 }
7111 {
7112 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Convert return value");
7113 Label finish_return;
7114 __ Branch(&finish_return, ne, return_value, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
7115 __ LoadRoot(return_value, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
7116 __ bind(&finish_return);
7117 }
7118
7119 __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
7120 AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
7121
7122 __ Ret();
7123
7124 if (with_profiling) {
7125 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
7126 __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
7127 // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
7128 MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7129 ER::api_callback_thunk_argument_address(isolate), no_reg);
7130 __ StoreWord(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
7131 __ li(scratch, thunk_ref);
7132 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
7133 __ Branch(&done_api_call);
7134 }
7135
7136 __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
7137 __ bind(&propagate_exception);
7138 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
7139
7140 {
7141 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
7142 masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
7143 __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
7144 __ StoreWord(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
7145 // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
7146 Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
7147 __ Move(saved_result, a0);
7148 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, prev_level_reg);
7149 __ li(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address(isolate));
7150 __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
7151 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], saved_result);
7152 __ Branch(&leave_exit_frame);
7153 }
7154}
7155
7156void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
7157 Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
7158 Label done;
7159 // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
7160 LoadTaggedField(dst,
7161 FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
7162 LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
7163
7164 // Check if feedback vector is valid.
7165 LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
7166 Lhu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
7167 Branch(&done, eq, scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));

7171 Branch(fbv_undef);

7173 bind(&done);
7174}
